{"type":"message","id":"3a022fe0","parentId":"555ad8a9","timestamp":"2026-04-19T03:39:09.331Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I've written the files directly. Now let me also write the architecture.md since the senior-architect agent failed twice. I have enough knowledge to write this myself.","thinkingSignature":"a3bb0f3803458048c2018bddbdc751803846ce570763a3173645662d1412808e"},{"type":"text","text":"Giờ viết luôn architecture.md:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_u3m3penbgufw_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-knowledge-hub/openspec/changes/tech-blog/architecture.md","content":"# System Architecture: AHV Tech Knowledge Hub\n\n**Created:** 2026-04-19 | **Author:** Orbis (Master Orchestrator)\n\n---\n\n## 1. Next.js 14 App Router — Folder Structure\n\n```\nahv-knowledge-hub/\n├── app/                          # App Router\n│   ├── layout.tsx                # Root layout (fonts, providers, metadata)\n│   ├── page.tsx                  # Home page\n│   ├── globals.css               # Tailwind + custom CSS variables\n│   │\n│   ├── articles/                 # Blog routes\n│   │   ├── page.tsx              # Articles listing (/articles)\n│   │   ├── [slug]/\n│   │   │   ├── page.tsx         # Article detail (/articles/[slug])\n│   │   │   └──opengraph-image.tsx\n│   │   └── category/\n│   │       └── [category]/\n│   │           └── page.tsx     # Category listing\n│   │\n│   ├── music/\n│   │   └── page.tsx             # Relaxation zone (/music)\n│   │\n│   ├── study/\n│   │   ├── page.tsx             # Live study room list\n│   │   └── [roomId]/\n│   │       └── page.tsx         # Specific room (/study/abc123)\n│   │\n│   ├── search/\n│   │   └── page.tsx             # Search results\n│   │\n│   ├── about/\n│   │   └── page.tsx\n│   │\n│   ├── sitemap.ts               # Dynamic sitemap\n│   └── robots.ts                # Dynamic robots.txt\n│\n├── components/\n│   ├── ui/                      # shadcn/ui base components\n│   │   ├── button.tsx\n│   │   ├── card.tsx\n│   │   ├── input.tsx\n│   │   └── ...\n│   │\n│   ├── layout/                  # App-wide layout components\n│   │   ├── header.tsx\n│   │   ├── footer.tsx\n│   │   ├── sidebar.tsx\n│   │   └── mobile-nav.tsx\n│   │\n│   ├── blog/                    # Blog-specific components\n│   │   ├── article-card.tsx\n│   │   ├── article-content.tsx\n│   │   ├── table-of-contents.tsx\n│   │   ├── code-block.tsx\n│   │   ├── author-card.tsx\n│   │   └── share-buttons.tsx\n│   │\n│   ├── music/                  # Music player components\n│   │   ├── music-player.tsx\n│   │   ├── mini-player.tsx\n│   │   ├── playlist.tsx\n│   │   ├── mood-selector.tsx\n│   │   └── audio-visualizer.tsx\n│   │\n│   ├── study/                  # Live study components\n│   │   ├── pomodoro-timer.tsx\n│   │   ├── participant-list.tsx\n│   │   ├── study-goal.tsx\n│   │   ├── room-join.tsx\n│   │   └── ambient-selector.tsx\n│   │\n│   ├── seo/                    # SEO components\n│   │   ├── json-ld.tsx\n│   │   ├── article-schema.tsx\n│   │   └── breadcrumbs.tsx\n│   │\n│   └── shared/                 # Cross-cutting components\n│       ├── theme-toggle.tsx\n│       ├── newsletter-form.tsx\n│       ├── loading-skeleton.tsx\n│       └── error-boundary.tsx\n│\n├── content/                     # MDX content files\n│   ├── articles/\n│   │   ├── ctdl/\n│   │   │   ├── binary-search.mdx\n│   │   │   ├── linked-list.mdx\n│   │   │   └── dynamic-programming.mdx\n│   │   ├── ai/\n│   │   │   ├── neural-network-from-scratch.mdx\n│   │   │   └── linear-regression.mdx\n│   │   ├── web-dev/\n│   │   │   ├── nextjs-app-router.mdx\n│   │   │   └── docker-compose.mdx\n│   │   └── ...\n│   │\n│   └── authors/\n│       └── ahv-tech-hub.mdx    # Author bio\n│\n├── lib/\n│   ├── content.ts               # MDX loader + processing pipeline\n│   ├── mongodb.ts              # MongoDB client singleton\n│   ├── socket.ts               # Socket.IO client singleton\n│   ├── seo.ts                  # SEO helpers\n│   └── utils.ts                # Shared utilities\n│\n├── models/                     # MongoDB Mongoose schemas\n│   ├── article.ts\n│   ├── tag.ts\n│   ├── author.ts\n│   ├── study-room.ts\n│   └── session.ts\n│\n├── server/\n│   ├── server.ts               # Custom server for Socket.IO\n│   └── socket/\n│       ├── index.ts            # Socket.IO setup\n│       └── handlers/\n│           ├── study-room.ts   # Room join/leave/leaves\n│           └── presence.ts    # Real-time presence\n│\n├── hooks/                      # Custom React hooks\n│   ├── use-socket.ts\n│   ├── use-pomodoro.ts\n│   ├── use-music-player.ts\n│   └── use-search.ts\n│\n├── providers/\n│   ├── theme-provider.tsx\n│   ├── music-provider.tsx      # Context for persistent player\n│   └── socket-provider.tsx\n│\n├── config/\n│   ├── site.ts                 # Site-wide config (name, URL, social)\n│   └── categories.ts           # Category definitions\n│\n├── public/\n│   ├── images/\n│   ├── fonts/\n│   └── og-images/\n│\n└── scripts/\n    └── seed-content.ts        # Seed initial MDX articles\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. Data Flow\n\n### Content Pipeline (MDX → UI)\n```\ncontent/articles/ctdl/binary-search.mdx\n         │\n         ▼\nlib/content.ts (gray-matter + next-mdx-remote)\n         │\n         ├─► Frontmatter: { title, date, category, tags, excerpt, author, hero }\n         │\n         └─► MDX Body ──► MDX Components (code-block, callout, etc.)\n                           │\n                           ▼\n                    Article page (app/articles/[slug]/page.tsx)\n                           │\n                           ├─► JSON-LD (Article schema)\n                           ├─► TOC generation (from H2/H3 headings)\n                           └─► Related posts (by category/tags)\n```\n\n### Article Reading (Static + ISR)\n```\nBuild time:   MDX files → Static HTML + JSON at build\n               │\nRuntime:      Request ──► ISR revalidate: 3600s (1h)\n                          or on-demand revalidation via webhook\n               │\n               └─► Next.js Edge Cache ──► Browser\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. Component Architecture\n\n### Shared vs Feature-Based\n| Pattern | Components | When to use |\n|---------|-----------|-------------|\n| **Shared** | Button, Input, Card, Badge, Modal | Cross-cutting, used everywhere |\n| **Feature-based** | ArticleCard, MusicPlayer, PomodoroTimer | Domain-specific, self-contained |\n| **Page-level** | Header, Footer, Sidebar, TOC | Only in specific pages |\n\n### State Management\n| State Type | Solution | Example |\n|-----------|---------|---------|\n| Global UI | React Context | Theme, Music player, Socket connection |\n| Server data | Server Components + fetch | Article content, category lists |\n| Client data | React hooks (useState/useReducer) | Timer state, form inputs |\n| Real-time | Socket.IO context | Study room participants |\n| URL state | nuqs or URLSearchParams | Search filters, pagination |\n\n### Music Player State (Persistent)\n```\nMusicProvider (context) — persists across page navigation\n  │\n  ├─► currentTrack: Track | null\n  ├─► isPlaying: boolean\n  ├─► volume: number\n  ├─► playlist: Track[]\n  └─► queue: Track[]\n\nMiniPlayer (bottom bar) always mounted in root layout\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. Real-time Architecture (Socket.IO + Next.js)\n\n### Custom Server Setup\nSince Next.js App Router doesn't natively support Socket.IO, use a custom server:\n\n**server/server.ts:**\n```typescript\nimport { createServer } from 'http'\nimport { parse } from 'url'\nimport next from 'next'\nimport { Server as SocketIOServer } from 'socket.io'\n\nconst dev = process.env.NODE_ENV !== 'production'\nconst app = next({ dev })\nconst handle = app.getRequestHandler()\n\napp.prepare().then(() => {\n  const httpServer = createServer((req, res) => {\n    const parsedUrl = parse(req.url!, true)\n    handle(req, res, parsedUrl)\n  })\n\n  const io = new SocketIOServer(httpServer, {\n    cors: { origin: '*', methods: ['GET', 'POST'] }\n  })\n\n  // Attach io to req so API routes can access\n  httpServer.on('request', (req: any, res: any) => {\n    req.io = io\n  })\n\n  // Socket event handlers\n  io.on('connection', (socket) => {\n    // Join study room\n    socket.on('join-room', ({ roomId, username }) => {\n      socket.join(roomId)\n      io.to(roomId).emit('user-joined', { username, id: socket.id })\n      // Broadcast participant count\n      const room = io.sockets.adapter.rooms.get(roomId)\n      io.to(roomId).emit('room-count', room?.size ?? 0)\n    })\n\n    // Leave room\n    socket.on('leave-room', ({ roomId, username }) => {\n      socket.leave(roomId)\n      io.to(roomId).emit('user-left', { username, id: socket.id })\n    })\n\n    // Pomodoro sync\n    socket.on('pomodoro-tick', ({ roomId, timeLeft, phase }) => {\n      socket.to(roomId).emit('pomodoro-sync', { timeLeft, phase })\n    })\n  })\n\n  httpServer.listen(3000, () => {\n    console.log('> Ready on http://localhost:3000')\n  })\n})\n```\n\n### Socket.IO Rooms\n| Event | Payload | Description |\n|-------|---------|-------------|\n| `join-room` | `{ roomId, username }` | User joins a study room |\n| `leave-room` | `{ roomId, username }` | User leaves |\n| `user-joined` | `{ username, id }` | Broadcast to room |\n| `user-left` | `{ username, id }` | Broadcast to room |\n| `room-count` | `number` | Participant count |\n| `pomodoro-sync` | `{ timeLeft, phase }` | Timer sync across clients |\n\n---\n\n## 5. Music Integration Strategy\n\n### Embed vs Custom Player\n\n**Decision: Hybrid approach**\n- YouTube embeds for visual/playlist content (YouTube Player API)\n- Spotify embeds for audio playlists (Spotify Web Playback SDK — future Phase 2)\n- Custom mini-player for persistent playback across navigation\n\n### YouTube Integration\n```typescript\n// components/music/youtube-player.tsx\n'use client'\nimport { useEffect, useRef, useState } from 'react'\n\nexport function useYouTubePlayer() {\n  const [player, setPlayer] = useState<YT.Player>()\n  const playerRef = useRef<YT.Player>()\n\n  useEffect(() => {\n    // Load YouTube IFrame API\n    if (!window.YT) {\n      const tag = document.createElement('script')\n      tag.src = 'https://www.youtube.com/iframe_api'\n      document.head.appendChild(tag)\n    }\n    // ... player initialization\n  }, [])\n\n  return { player, play, pause, loadVideo, seekTo }\n}\n```\n\n### Music Page Layout\n```\n/music page\n├── MoodSelector (client)\n├── YouTubePlayer (iframe embed)\n├── PlaylistSidebar (static)\n└── MiniPlayer (global, in root layout)\n```\n\n---\n\n## 6. SEO Architecture (App Router)\n\n### Metadata API (App Router native)\n```typescript\n// app/articles/[slug]/page.tsx\nexport async function generateMetadata({ params }: { params: { slug: string } }) {\n  const article = await getArticle(params.slug)\n  return {\n    title: `${article.title} | AHV Tech Hub`,\n    description: article.excerpt,\n    openGraph: {\n      type: 'article',\n      title: article.title,\n      description: article.excerpt,\n      images: [{ url: article.hero, width: 1200, height: 630 }],\n      publishedTime: article.date,\n      tags: article.tags,\n    },\n    twitter: {\n      card: 'summary_large_image',\n      title: article.title,\n      description: article.excerpt,\n      images: [article.hero],\n    },\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### JSON-LD Component\n```tsx\n// components/seo/article-schema.tsx\nexport function ArticleSchema({ article }: { article: Article }) {\n  const schema = {\n    '@context': 'https://schema.org',\n    '@type': 'Article',\n    headline: article.title,\n    description: article.excerpt,\n    image: article.hero,\n    author: { '@type': 'Person', name: 'AHV Tech Hub' },\n    publisher: { '@type': 'Organization', name: 'AHV Tech Hub' },\n    datePublished: article.date,\n    mainEntityOfPage: { '@type': 'WebPage', '@id': article.url },\n  }\n  return <script type=\"application/ld+json\" dangerouslySetInnerHTML={{ __html: JSON.stringify(schema) }} />\n}\n```\n\n### Sitemap (App Router)\n```typescript\n// app/sitemap.ts\nimport { MetadataRoute } from 'next'\nimport { getAllArticles } from '@/lib/content'\n\nexport default async function sitemap(): Promise<MetadataRoute.Sitemap> {\n  const articles = await getAllArticles()\n  const baseUrl = 'https://ahvtechhub.com'\n\n  return [\n    { url: baseUrl, lastModified: new Date(), changeFrequency: 'daily', priority: 1 },\n    { url: `${baseUrl}/articles`, lastModified: new Date(), changeFrequency: 'weekly', priority: 0.9 },\n    { url: `${baseUrl}/music`, lastModified: new Date(), changeFrequency: 'monthly', priority: 0.7 },\n    { url: `${baseUrl}/study`, lastModified: new Date(), changeFrequency: 'weekly', priority: 0.8 },\n    ...articles.map(a => ({\n      url: `${baseUrl}/articles/${a.slug}`,\n      lastModified: new Date(a.date),\n      changeFrequency: 'monthly' as const,\n      priority: 0.8,\n    })),\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 7. MongoDB Collections Preview\n\n```typescript\n// models/article.ts\n{\n  _id: ObjectId,\n  slug: string,           // unique, URL-safe\n  title: string,\n  excerpt: string,        // 150-200 chars for SEO\n  content: string,         // MDX content (or reference to MDX file)\n  category: 'ctdl' | 'ai' | 'web-dev' | 'devops' | 'cs-fundamentals',\n  tags: string[],\n  hero: string,           // URL to hero image\n  author: ObjectId,        // ref: Author\n  readingTime: number,     // minutes\n  publishedAt: Date,\n  updatedAt: Date,\n  status: 'draft' | 'published',\n  seo: {\n    metaTitle: string,\n    metaDescription: string,\n    canonicalUrl: string,\n  }\n}\n\n// models/study-room.ts\n{\n  _id: ObjectId,\n  roomId: string,         // 6-char code, e.g. \"ABC123\"\n  name: string,            // e.g. \"CTDL Practice Room\"\n  createdBy: string,      // username\n  participants: [{\n    socketId: string,\n    username: string,\n    joinedAt: Date,\n  }],\n  pomodoro: {\n    workMinutes: number,  // default 25\n    breakMinutes: number, // default 5\n    longBreakMinutes: number,\n  },\n  isActive: boolean,\n  createdAt: Date,\n}\n\n// models/author.ts\n{\n  _id: ObjectId,\n  slug: string,\n  name: string,\n  bio: string,\n  avatar: string,\n  social: { twitter?: string, github?: string },\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 8. Environment Variables\n\n```bash\n# .env.local (never commit)\nMONGODB_URI=mongodb+srv://user:pass@cluster.mongodb.net/ahv-knowledge-hub\nMONGODB_DB=ahv-knowledge-hub\n\n# Optional: Analytics (Phase 2)\nNEXT_PUBLIC_GA_ID=G-XXXXXXXXXX\n\n# Optional: YouTube API (for playlist fetching)\nYOUTUBE_API_KEY=AIza...\n\n# Site URL (for absolute URLs in metadata)\nNEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=https://ahvtechhub.com\n```\n\n---\n\n## 9. ISR Strategy\n\n| Route | Revalidation | Strategy |\n|-------|-------------|----------|\n| `/` (Home) | 3600s (1h) | ISR + on-demand on new article publish |\n| `/articles` | 1800s (30min) | ISR |\n| `/articles/[slug]` | 86400s (24h) | ISR + on-demand on article update |\n| `/music` | 86400s | ISR (playlists change rarely) |\n| `/study` | 300s (5min) | ISR (room list) |\n| `/study/[roomId]` | 0 (SSR) | SSR (real-time, no cache) |\n\n**On-demand Revalidation:** POST `/api/revalidate?secret=TOKEN&path=/articles/[slug]`\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":231,"output":3911,"cacheRead":36276,"cacheWrite":11993,"totalTokens":52411,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776569892917,"responseId":"063381265f42c447fd0234350ef3ed5f"}}
