{"type":"message","id":"c504bc93","parentId":"e8fc5e6d","timestamp":"2026-04-19T05:09:01.027Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The homepage has some article-related content. Let me check if the MDX articles render. The issue might be that the MDX serialization in `lib/content.ts` is using `serialize` from `next-mdx-remote/serialize` which is client-side. For Next.js App Router, I should be using `next-mdx-remote/rsc` instead.\n\nLet me check the content.ts file again and fix the MDX rendering for App Router server components.","thinkingSignature":"b16eb86ada5839e2dc8af6b13fc526847bb7097f3d16ece522218b17ead848f6"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_gipr4fhe6gkd_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/maiy-tech-hub && grep -n \"next-mdx-remote\" lib/content.ts"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":79,"output":154,"cacheRead":112552,"cacheWrite":255,"totalTokens":113040,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776575335082,"responseId":"0633966879918bd64e68343fe99eae75"}}
{"type":"message","id":"3ce8dd11","parentId":"c504bc93","timestamp":"2026-04-19T05:09:01.121Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_gipr4fhe6gkd_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"5:import { serialize } from 'next-mdx-remote/serialize'\n9:import type { MDXRemoteSerializeResult } from 'next-mdx-remote'"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":39,"aggregated":"5:import { serialize } from 'next-mdx-remote/serialize'\n9:import type { MDXRemoteSerializeResult } from 'next-mdx-remote'","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776575341096}}
{"type":"message","id":"e94dbd5d","parentId":"3ce8dd11","timestamp":"2026-04-19T05:09:14.354Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is that `serialize` from `next-mdx-remote/serialize` is a client-side function. For Next.js App Router with Server Components, I need to use `next-mdx-remote/rsc` which provides `MDXRemote` as a server component.\n\nLet me fix this.","thinkingSignature":"38253053df7c7304955a41c50b5c95738d2b89cb272d18d145b7bcceb6000578"},{"type":"text","text":"Vấn đề rồi — dùng `serialize` (client-side) thay vì RSC. Fix ngay:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_d0o2vh6dmerq_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/maiy-tech-hub/lib/content.ts","content":"import fs from 'fs'\nimport path from 'path'\nimport matter from 'gray-matter'\nimport readingTime from 'reading-time'\nimport { MDXRemote } from 'next-mdx-remote/rsc'\nimport remarkGfm from 'remark-gfm'\nimport rehypeSlug from 'rehype-slug'\nimport rehypeAutolinkHeadings from 'rehype-autolink-headings'\nimport type { ArticleSummary } from '@/components/blog/article-card'\n\nconst CONTENT_DIR = path.join(process.cwd(), 'content', 'articles')\n\nexport interface Article extends ArticleSummary {\n  content: React.ComponentType\n}\n\nfunction getArticleFiles(): string[] {\n  if (!fs.existsSync(CONTENT_DIR)) return []\n  return fs\n    .readdirSync(CONTENT_DIR)\n    .filter((f) => f.endsWith('.mdx') || f.endsWith('.md'))\n}\n\nexport async function getAllArticles(): Promise<ArticleSummary[]> {\n  const files = getArticleFiles()\n  const articles = files.map((file) => {\n    const slug = file.replace(/\\.(mdx|md)$/, '')\n    const raw = fs.readFileSync(path.join(CONTENT_DIR, file), 'utf-8')\n    const { data, content } = matter(raw)\n    const rt = readingTime(content)\n\n    return {\n      slug,\n      title: data.title || slug,\n      excerpt: data.excerpt || '',\n      category: data.category || 'cs-fundamentals',\n      tags: data.tags || [],\n      hero: data.hero || null,\n      author: data.author || 'MAIY Tech Hub',\n      readingTime: Math.ceil(rt.minutes),\n      publishedAt: data.date || new Date().toISOString(),\n    } as ArticleSummary\n  })\n\n  return articles.sort(\n    (a, b) => new Date(b.publishedAt).getTime() - new Date(a.publishedAt).getTime()\n  )\n}\n\nexport async function getRecentArticles(limit = 6): Promise<ArticleSummary[]> {\n  const all = await getAllArticles()\n  return all.slice(0, limit)\n}\n\nexport async function getFeaturedArticles(): Promise<ArticleSummary[]> {\n  return getAllArticles()\n}\n\nexport async function getArticleBySlug(slug: string): Promise<Article | null> {\n  const mdxPath = path.join(CONTENT_DIR, `${slug}.mdx`)\n  const mdPath = path.join(CONTENT_DIR, `${slug}.md`)\n\n  const filePath = fs.existsSync(mdxPath)\n    ? mdxPath\n    : fs.existsSync(mdPath)\n    ? mdPath\n    : null\n\n  if (!filePath) return null\n\n  const raw = fs.readFileSync(filePath, 'utf-8')\n  const { data, content } = matter(raw)\n  const rt = readingTime(content)\n\n  return {\n    slug,\n    title: data.title || slug,\n    excerpt: data.excerpt || '',\n    category: data.category || 'cs-fundamentals',\n    tags: data.tags || [],\n    hero: data.hero || null,\n    author: data.author || 'MAIY Tech Hub',\n    readingTime: Math.ceil(rt.minutes),\n    publishedAt: data.date || new Date().toISOString(),\n    // Return raw MDX content as component for RSC rendering\n    content: async () => (\n      <MDXRemote\n        source={content}\n        options={{\n          mdxOptions: {\n            remarkPlugins: [remarkGfm],\n            rehypePlugins: [rehypeSlug, rehypeAutolinkHeadings],\n          },\n        }}\n      />\n    ),\n  }\n}\n\nexport async function getArticlesByCategory(\n  category: string\n): Promise<ArticleSummary[]> {\n  const all = await getAllArticles()\n  return all.filter((a) => a.category === category)\n}\n\nexport async function getAllSlugs(): Promise<string[]> {\n  return getArticleFiles().map((f) => f.replace(/\\.(mdx|md)$/, ''))\n}\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":112,"output":986,"cacheRead":112663,"cacheWrite":315,"totalTokens":114076,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776575341134,"responseId":"0633966e48cd172426cf76e87d084764"}}
