{"type":"message","id":"6ff37e2e","parentId":"e923a2f8","timestamp":"2026-04-19T05:20:11.803Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Lead wants me to continue proposing and implementing features without asking. Let me think about what else can be done to get to 95%+ completion for MAIY Tech Hub.\n\nCurrent state ~90%:\n- Pages: Home, Articles, Article detail, Music, Study, Search, About, Contribute ✅\n- Admin panel: Login, Dashboard, Articles management, Article editor ✅\n- Dark/light mode ✅\n- Lucide icons ✅\n- 10 MDX articles ✅\n- MDX rendering ✅\n- Reading progress bar ✅\n- Table of contents ✅\n- Social share ✅\n\n\n- Back to top ✅\n- Copy code button ✅\n- Articles sort ✅\n- Search with Fuse.js ✅\n- Category pages ✅\n- Newsletter form ✅\n- Related articles ✅\n- Loading skeletons ✅\n- Error boundary ✅\n- 404 page ✅\n- SEO: sitemap, robots, JSON-LD, breadcrumbs ✅\n- WebSite + Breadcrumb schemas ✅\n- ISR revalidation API ✅\n- PWA manifest ✅\n- Keyboard shortcut (Ctrl+K) ✅\n- Mini-player ✅\n- Pomodoro timer ✅\n- Ambient sounds ✅\n- E2E tests ✅\n- Responsive design ✅\n\nStill working through the final polish items—real-time chat in study rooms, comments, analytics, and ambient sound features are coming next.\n\nNow I'm thinking about what's missing to get to 95% completion. I could add a featured article section to highlight top content, implement a newsletter subscription API, create an article preview mode, improve the home page with better animations and scroll reveals, add article ratings or reading time estimates, and build a \"Contribute\" page for community submissions. I'll start implementing these in phases.\n\nI should check what's already in the workspace before spawning agents to avoid duplicating work. The plan is to create a newsletter API endpoint for subscriptions, add a featured articles toggle to frontmatter, enhance the home page with animated sections and hero animations, and implement comments using localStorage for persistence.\n\nActually, I'm realizing the comments feature needs a backend to work properly, so I'll focus on building the newsletter API, enhancing the hero section, adding an articles filter and pagination, and creating a featured article badge system instead.\n\nLet me start by building out the newsletter API to store subscriptions, then move on to the hero animation and article pagination improvements.","thinkingSignature":"487945bfa9c9aad91cfee4adb4a18f9c6dccc589817e56822fcab19a0ea05e67"},{"type":"text","text":"Lead cho phép tự làm — tiếp tục Phase cuối để đạt 95%+.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_cmqwmf9ws61m_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/maiy-tech-hub && git checkout -b feat/final-polish && echo \"On feat/final-polish\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":160,"output":572,"cacheRead":126865,"cacheWrite":541,"totalTokens":128138,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776575993749,"responseId":"063398fbd46856945cad0787b632a48f"}}
