{"type":"message","id":"267851b6","parentId":"9f6e9edf","timestamp":"2026-04-19T07:25:33.106Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The article page is rendering with the correct title and content. So the dev server is working. But Lead gets 404. \n\nThis is confusing. Maybe the lead was accessing the tunnel URL, and the tunnel had cached the old 404 response? Or maybe the lead was accessing a different slug?\n\nActually, let me re-read: \"404 khi đọc chi tiết một bài viết\" - 404 when reading article details. This was sent BEFORE the tunnel was set up. So he was trying localhost from his phone. Now he says he has his own VPS.\n\nWait, but even after the fix, if he's accessing from his phone via the tunnel, it should work since localhost shows 200. Unless the tunnel cached the 404.\n\n\nThe tunnel was established after his initial report, so it's likely still serving cached 404 responses. Let me verify the tunnel is returning the correct content now that the fix is deployed.","thinkingSignature":"9fc9f91a35535945c2bcfcb5e33e21aaa7b616fd98d347390bd11f2f8244641a"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_et86dkjehckz_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s -o /dev/null -w \"%{http_code}\" https://mechanisms-measures-your-britney.trycloudflare.com/articles/binary-search 2>/dev/null && echo \"\" && curl -s https://mechanisms-measures-your-britney.trycloudflare.com/articles/binary-search 2>/dev/null | grep -o \"<title>[^<]*</title>\"","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":117,"output":308,"cacheRead":162963,"cacheWrite":441,"totalTokens":163829,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776583522879,"responseId":"0633b664a61bf6afcb5fbedf46b24890"}}
