{"type":"message","id":"0f385630","parentId":"b9623249","timestamp":"2026-04-19T07:36:00.081Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Lead said to continue without asking. Let me build the real-time features for Study Room. I'll create:\n\n1. WebRTC service for peer connections\n2. Chat component (Socket.IO based)\n3. Video grid component\n4. Control bar (camera, mic, screen, leave)\n5. Update study page to integrate all\n\nSince we're in a real VPS environment, I'll use:\n- Socket.IO for signaling + text chat\n- WebRTC for video/audio/screen (using free STUN servers)\n- Simple approach that works without external services\n\nLet me start implementing.","thinkingSignature":"1ce7f62741bd3ded9cbaa683618e0d60e1b2e85542a5a6ad3e6ff511fe4b271a"},{"type":"text","text":"\n**Phase 1: WebRTC service + Chat + Video components:**\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_c5qg6zog8z9c_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/maiy-tech-hub/lib/webrtc.ts","content":"// WebRTC configuration with free STUN servers\nexport const RTC_CONFIG: RTCConfiguration = {\n  iceServers: [\n    { urls: 'stun:stun.l.google.com:19302' },\n    { urls: 'stun:stun1.l.google.com:19302' },\n    { urls: 'stun:stun.stunprotocol.org:3478' },\n  ],\n  iceCandidatePoolSize: 10,\n}\n\nexport interface PeerConnection {\n  peerId: string\n  peerName: string\n  connection: RTCPeerConnection\n  stream?: MediaStream\n  videoTrack?: MediaStreamTrack\n  audioTrack?: MediaStreamTrack\n  screenTrack?: MediaStreamTrack\n}\n\nexport type PeerEvent =\n  | { type: 'peer-joined'; peerId: string; peerName: string; stream?: MediaStream }\n  | { type: 'peer-left'; peerId: string }\n  | { type: 'offer'; from: string; sdp: RTCSessionDescriptionInit }\n  | { type: 'answer'; from: string; sdp: RTCSessionDescriptionInit }\n  | { type: 'ice-candidate'; from: string; candidate: RTCIceCandidateInit }\n  | { type: 'chat-message'; from: string; fromName: string; text: string; timestamp: number }\n  | { type: 'screen-share'; from: string; sharing: boolean }\n  | { type: 'connected'; peerId: string }\n  | { type: 'disconnected' }\n  | { type: 'error'; message: string }\n\nexport type PeerEventHandler = (event: PeerEvent) => void\n\nexport async function createPeerConnection(\n  peerId: string,\n  peerName: string,\n  onEvent: PeerEventHandler,\n  localStream?: MediaStream\n): Promise<PeerConnection> {\n  const pc = new RTCPeerConnection(RTC_CONFIG)\n  const peer: PeerConnection = {\n    peerId,\n    peerName,\n    connection: pc,\n  }\n\n  // Handle ICE candidates\n  pc.onicecandidate = (e) => {\n    if (e.candidate) {\n      onEvent({\n        type: 'ice-candidate',\n        from: peerId,\n        candidate: e.candidate.toJSON(),\n      })\n    }\n  }\n\n  // Handle incoming stream\n  pc.ontrack = (e) => {\n    const [remoteStream] = e.streams\n    if (remoteStream) {\n      peer.stream = remoteStream\n      peer.videoTrack = remoteStream.getVideoTracks()[0]\n      peer.audioTrack = remoteStream.getAudioTracks()[0]\n      onEvent({\n        type: 'peer-joined',\n        peerId,\n        peerName,\n        stream: remoteStream,\n      })\n    }\n  }\n\n  // Connection state\n  pc.onconnectionstatechange = () => {\n    if (pc.connectionState === 'connected') {\n      onEvent({ type: 'connected', peerId })\n    } else if (\n      pc.connectionState === 'disconnected' ||\n      pc.connectionState === 'failed'\n    ) {\n      onEvent({ type: 'disconnected' })\n    }\n  }\n\n  // Add local tracks\n  if (localStream) {\n    localStream.getTracks().forEach((track) => {\n      pc.addTrack(track, localStream)\n    })\n    peer.stream = localStream\n    peer.videoTrack = localStream.getVideoTracks()[0]\n    peer.audioTrack = localStream.getAudioTracks()[0]\n  }\n\n  return peer\n}\n\nexport async function createOffer(pc: RTCPeerConnection): Promise<RTCSessionDescriptionInit> {\n  const offer = await pc.createOffer()\n  await pc.setLocalDescription(offer)\n  return offer\n}\n\nexport async function createAnswer(\n  pc: RTCPeerConnection,\n  offer: RTCSessionDescriptionInit\n): Promise<RTCSessionDescriptionInit> {\n  await pc.setRemoteDescription(new RTCSessionDescription(offer))\n  const answer = await pc.createAnswer()\n  await pc.setLocalDescription(answer)\n  return answer\n}\n\nexport async function handleAnswer(\n  pc: RTCPeerConnection,\n  answer: RTCSessionDescriptionInit\n): Promise<void> {\n  await pc.setRemoteDescription(new RTCSessionDescription(answer))\n}\n\nexport async function addIceCandidate(\n  pc: RTCPeerConnection,\n  candidate: RTCIceCandidateInit\n): Promise<void> {\n  await pc.addIceCandidate(new RTCIceCandidate(candidate))\n}\n\nexport async function getLocalStream(\n  video: boolean = true,\n  audio: boolean = true\n): Promise<MediaStream | null> {\n  try {\n    const stream = await navigator.mediaDevices.getUserMedia({\n      video: video\n        ? { width: { ideal: 1280 }, height: { ideal: 720 }, facingMode: 'user' }\n        : false,\n      audio: audio ? { echoCancellation: true, noiseSuppression: true } : false,\n    })\n    return stream\n  } catch (err) {\n    console.warn('MediaDevices error:', err)\n    return null\n  }\n}\n\nexport async function getScreenStream(): Promise<MediaStream | null> {\n  try {\n    const stream = await navigator.mediaDevices.getDisplayMedia({\n      video: { cursor: 'always' } as MediaTrackConstraints,\n      audio: false,\n    })\n    return stream\n  } catch {\n    return null\n  }\n}\n\nexport function stopStream(stream?: MediaStream) {\n  stream?.getTracks().forEach((t) => t.stop())\n}\n\nexport function toggleTrack(track?: MediaStreamTrack, enabled?: boolean) {\n  if (track) track.enabled = enabled ?? !track.enabled\n}\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":136,"output":1368,"cacheRead":169443,"cacheWrite":518,"totalTokens":171465,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cac