{"type":"compaction","id":"e7ba148a","parentId":"5479d7ff","timestamp":"2026-04-19T07:37:14.008Z","summary":"## Goal\nBuild \"MAIY Tech Hub\" — a modern IT knowledge blog with Next.js 14, featuring: blog articles (CTDL, AI, Web Dev, DevOps, CS Fundamentals), music relaxation zone, live study rooms with Pomodoro timer, SEO-optimized content in Vietnamese. Lead approved self-merge into `develop` without review. Agent is authorized to continue adding features proactively until product is 90%+ feature complete.\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- Project under GitLab group `maiy-hub` (`https://gitlab.com/maiy-hub/maiy-tech-hub`)\n- Git workflow: feature branch → MR → merge (Lead approved self-merge, no review needed)\n- No pushing directly to `develop` (but self-merge is allowed)\n- All emoji icons replaced with Lucide React throughout\n- Continue until product is 95%+ complete without waiting for Lead approval\n- All requests from Lead to go through prompt-optimizer agent before execution\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] **Git workflow fixed** — feat/scaffold-initial → develop (fast-forward merge), MR !1 created and closed\n- [x] **Icon refresh** — All raw emojis replaced with Lucide React: header (💡→Lightbulb), footer, newsletter (⏳→Loader2, 🎉→PartyPopper), home page (🚀→Rocket, 🎵→Headphones, 📚→BookOpen), music page (🎯→Target, 😴→Moon, ⚡→Zap, 📚→BookOpen), study page (🌧️→CloudRain, ☕→Coffee, 📖→BookOpen, ⏱️→Timer, 🎯→Target)\n- [x] **MDX rendering fixed** — switched from `next-mdx-remote/serialize` to `next-mdx-remote/rsc` (RSC-compatible); article detail pages now render full MDX content properly with 28/28 pages\n- [x] **Phase 4 SEO Audit** (seo-audit subagent) — created: `app/api/revalidate/route.ts`, `components/seo/web-site-schema.tsx`, `components/seo/breadcrumb-schema.tsx`, `app/about/page.tsx`, `.env.example`; updated `app/layout.tsx` with WebSiteSchema\n- [x] **Phase 4 E2E Tests** (playwright-pro subagent) — created `tests/e2e/` with home.spec.ts, articles.spec.ts, music.spec.ts, study.spec.ts, search.spec.ts, seo.spec.ts (16 tests total); created `playwright.config.ts`; installed `@playwright/test@1.59.1` + Chromium\n- [x] **Phase 5 MDX Renderer** — `next.config.mjs` configured with `@next/mdx`, remark-gfm, rehype-slug, rehype-autolink-headings; `mdx-components.tsx` created; MDXContent component with custom Callout, CodeBlock, copy button\n- [x] **Phase 5 PWA + Polish** — `public/manifest.json`, `public/favicon.svg` (SVG with gradient), `components/layout/keyboard-shortcut.tsx` (Ctrl+K), stats bar on home page, better prose styles in globals.css, `KeyboardShortcuts` added to layout\n- [x] **Phase 6 Admin Panel** — `lib/auth.ts` (httpOnly cookie sessions, env var password), `app/admin/login/page.tsx`, `app/admin/layout.tsx` (auth guard, nav), `app/admin/page.tsx` (dashboard with stats + quick actions), `app/admin/articles/page.tsx` (table with CRUD), `app/admin/articles/new/page.tsx` (MDX frontmatter form), `app/api/auth/login/route.ts`, `app/api/auth/logout/route.ts`, `app/api/admin/articles/route.ts`; admin password: `maiy2026`\n- [x] **Phase 6 Animations** (framer-motion) — `AnimatedArticleCard` (hover lift + stagger), `AnimateOnScroll` (IntersectionObserver-triggered), `StaggerContainer`/`StaggerItem`, `HeroAnimated` (animated gradient orbs + stagger entrance)\n- [x] **Phase 6 Study Rooms Real-time** — `hooks/use-socket.ts` updated with joinRoom/leaveRoom/syncPomodoro; study page fully rewritten with Socket.IO events (user-joined, user-left, pomodoro-sync), connection status indicator, animated participants, phase transitions with motion\n- [x] **Phase 7 Final Polish** — `app/api/newsletter/route.ts` (Zod validation), `NewsletterForm` with real API call + loading/error states, `HeroAnimated` with gradient orbs + animated text, featured badge on article cards, `ArticlesFilter` (search + category + sort combined), `SearchContent` with keyboard nav + category pills, 2 new MDX articles: `react-hooks-deep-dive.mdx` and `css-grid-master.mdx` (total 10 MDX articles)\n- [x] **Build verified**: 28/28 static pages ✅\n- [x] **Dev server running** at http://localhost:3000 (confirmed 200 OK on heartbeat)\n- [x] **All feature branches merged to develop** via self-merge workflow\n\n### In Progress\n- [none — project at 95%, Lead reviewing at localhost:3000]\n\n### Blocked\n- [none]\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **Self-merge approved**: Lead authorized agent to merge directly to `develop` without MR review\n- **Icon strategy**: Lucide React used exclusively throughout (FontAwesome avoided as requested — Lucide is more modern/lightweight)\n- **MDX rendering**: `next-mdx-remote/rsc` used for App Router Server Components compatibility (not the older `serialize` function)\n- **Admin auth**: Simple httpOnly cookie + env var password (production should use proper JWT/session)\n- **Real-time rooms**: Socket.IO on same Next.js port (custom server); degrades gracefully to offline mode\n- **Socket.IO path**: `SOCKET_URL` env var at port 3000 with websocket + polling transports\n\n## Next Steps\n1. **Lead review** at http://localhost:3000 — awaiting feedback\n2. **Remaining ~5%**: Comments system (needs backend/DB), analytics integration (Vercel Analytics), performance/Core Web Vitals optimization\n3. **Production deployment**: Vercel (for Next.js) + proper Socket.IO server (separate process or serverless-compatible alternative like Ably/Pusher)\n\n## Critical Context\n- **GitLab repo**: `https://gitlab.com/maiy-hub/maiy-tech-hub`\n- **Workspace path**: `/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/maiy-tech-hub/`\n- **Git remote 'maiy'**: `https://khuowgn:[token]@gitlab.com/maiy-hub/maiy-tech-hub.git`\n- **Admin password**: `maiy2026` (set via `ADMIN_PASSWORD` env var)\n- **Current develop HEAD**: `1b4acb9` (feat/final-polish merged)\n- **Total pages**: 28/28 static pages\n- **Article count**: 10 MDX articles across 5 categories\n- **Dev server PID**: 469698 (port 3000, confirmed 200 OK)\n- **MEMORY updated**: `/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/MEMORY.md`\n\n---\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n## Original Request\nUser asked the assistant to continue pushing the project to 100% and implement all remaining features without asking.\n\n## Early Progress\n- Created new branch `feat/100-percent`\n- Implemented **Tags page** (`/app/tags/page.tsx`) — shows all tags sorted by frequency with article counts\n- Implemented **Contact page** (`/app/contact/page.tsx`) — GitHub, email, article suggestions, contribution guide\n- Implemented **Privacy Policy** and **Terms of Service** pages\n- Created **ReadingHistory component** with localStorage tracking (saves last 10 read article slugs)\n- Improved **404 page** with gradient 404 text and navigation links (home, articles, search)\n- Updated **Footer** with all new links (tags, contact, privacy, terms, contribute)\n- Added Tags and Contact links to **Header navigation**\n- Updated **ThemeProvider** to enable smooth theme transitions (`disableTransitionOnChange={false}`)\n- Created **TrackerWrapper** client component to track article reading history in localStorage\n\n## Context for Suffix\n- The article page (`/app/articles/[slug]/page.tsx`) was being updated to include the `TrackerWrapper` component — added the import and inserted `<TrackerWrapper slug={params.slug} />` into the JSX return statement\n- Additional features were planned but not yet started: better code syntax highlighting, canonical URLs for SEO, Twitter card metadata, and a tags browsing page\n\n<read-files>\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/maiy-tech-hub/server/server.ts\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/skills/master-orchestrator/SKILL.md\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/prompt-optimizer/SKILL.md\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/prompt-optimizer/skills/prompt-optimizer/SKILL.md\n</read-files>\n\n<modified-files>\n/root/.openclaw/openclaw2.json\n/root/