i`, there could be a mismatch when filtering or displaying articles, though that wouldn't explain the `ENOENT` error I'm seeing.\n\nWait, let me reconsider the URL construction in `article-card.tsx` — if the slug is `linear-regression-python` from the filename, then clicking the card would generate `/articles/linear-regression-python`, but I need to verify what the actual slug value is when it's passed to the card component.\n\nLooking at the frontmatter structure, the title and other metadata are being extracted correctly, but I'm wondering if the category field is causing issues. The ENOENT error specifically means the file path `/content/articles/linear-regression-python.mdx` doesn't exist — it's missing the `ai/` subdirectory. Let me trace through how `getArticleBySlug` constructs the file path to see where the category information gets lost. I'm noticing the category mismatch—`AI` in the frontmatter versus `ai` in the route—but that wouldn't cause an ENOENT error. Let me trace through the article card slug construction to see if that's where the file path is getting malformed.","thinkingSignature":"a5d3863d5a9068994528e21f4164fb591453e34df8b0edebf03c399d2db6eb5e"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_7pzwtomoi31e_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/maiy-tech-hub/content/articles/ai/linear-regression-python.mdx","limit":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":393,"output":703,"cacheRead":64334,"cacheWrite":714,"totalTokens":66144,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776585440785,"responseId":"0633bde214f0eb56a070c55db1f432cc"}}
