{"type":"message","id":"ee772830","parentId":"8c7cdbd4","timestamp":"2026-04-19T07:58:09.237Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting! The server IS returning 200 for `/articles/linear-regression-python`. So the recursive find IS working in the running code.\n\nThe issue the Lead is seeing might be:\n1. The Lead was hitting a cached 404 from before the recursive find was implemented\n2. Some other article slug\n\nBut the Lead said \"linear-regression-python\" and the error was `ENOENT: .../content/articles/linear-regression-python.mdx`. That path has no subdirectory, which means the OLD code (without recursive find) was running.\n\nBut we just confirmed 200. So either:\n1. The server was restarted after I fixed it (and it now works)\n\n\n2. The Lead refreshed and it works now\n\nActually, wait - I see what happened now. Looking back at the execution history, the server was killed and restarted multiple times. The latest restart happened AFTER the fix was committed and pushed. So the currently running server should have the fix, and we just verified it's returning 200 for that URL. The Lead probably just needs to refresh their page.\n\nBut the error message itself is puzzling - it says the file `/content/articles/linear-regression-python.mdx` doesn't exist, which suggests the slug extraction or path construction might be off. Let me think through how the slug is being generated from the URL and whether it matches what the code is actually looking for.\n\nLooking at the `getAllArticles` function, it strips the `.mdx` extension from filenames, so a file like `linear-regression-python.mdx` becomes the slug `linear-regression-python`. But when `getArticleBySlug` tries to find it, it's searching recursively through subdirectories - and that's where the path mismatch might be occurring. The function might be looking for the file in a different location than where it's actually stored. I'm wondering if the issue is with file system caching or if the production build is actually stale. Let me rebuild to verify the fix is working correctly, then check the running server to see what's actually being served.","thinkingSignature":"cc0f926841e509880ca6e4de6cee1ba941059db2f584b9db410a4dfc5b53f9bb"},{"type":"text","text":"Server trả 200 rồi ✅ — fix đã hoạt động. Lead refresh trình duyệt là được.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_m5hgmsqifmkc_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"for slug in linear-regression-python neural-network-from-scratch stack-heap-memory github-actions-ci-cd docker-compose; do\n  code=$(curl -s -o /dev/null -w \"%{http_code}\" http://localhost:3000/articles/$slug)\n  echo \"$code /articles/$slug\"\ndone","timeout":20}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":79,"output":543,"cacheRead":65374,"cacheWrite":1267,"totalTokens":67263,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776585473541,"responseId":"0633be04e0e30ec0c0c09a7dd238b30a"}}
