{"type":"message","id":"7350dac2","parentId":"228f32de","timestamp":"2026-04-19T07:58:46.347Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"4191\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"6053576134\",\n  \"sender\": \"Khương Nịnh\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sun 2026-04-19 07:58 UTC\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Khương Nịnh (6053576134)\",\n  \"id\": \"6053576134\",\n  \"name\": \"Khương Nịnh\",\n  \"username\": \"khuowgn\"\n}\n```\n\ntính năng bật mic, bật cam, chia sẻ màn hình chưa hoạt động được"}],"timestamp":1776585526307}}
{"type":"message","id":"66d5f148","parentId":"7350dac2","timestamp":"2026-04-19T07:58:55.838Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Lead is saying the mic, camera, and screen share features are not working in the study room. Let me investigate the issue. The problem could be:\n\n1. The WebSocket signaling might not be working properly (offer/answer/ice-candidate exchange)\n2. The WebRTC connection might not be establishing properly\n3. The media streams might not be connecting between peers\n\nLet me check the study room page and the study-room component to debug.\n\nThe key issues could be:\n1. The WebSocket URL passed to the StudyRoom might be wrong - it uses `ws://${window.location.host}` but the server is running at port 3000, and WebSocket is at root path `/`\n\n\n2. STUN servers should work for basic WebRTC on the same network, but the offer/answer exchange might be failing somewhere\n\nI need to trace through the study room page and component to understand how the WebSocket URL is being constructed and whether the signaling flow is actually working.","thinkingSignature":"d64170db062d2aba0b27d4a23720f44f16076d165c954b4ba78adb5991255d5a"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_565pfgqjam68_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/maiy-tech-hub/app/study/page.tsx","offset":50,"limit":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":0,"output":271,"cacheRead":64758,"cacheWrite":745,"totalTokens":65774,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776585526347,"responseId":"0633be38bd25f732416665b538616f11"}}
{"type":"message","id":"97c3160f","parentId":"66d5f148","timestamp":"2026-04-19T07:58:55.890Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_565pfgqjam68_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"      color: 'text-orange-500',\n    },\n  ]\n\n  const handleJoinRoom = (e: React.FormEvent) => {\n    e.preventDefault()\n    if (!roomId.trim() || !username.trim()) return\n    const wsProtocol = window.location.protocol === 'https:' ? 'wss:' : 'ws:'\n    const wsUrl = `${wsProtocol}//${window.location.host}`\n    router.push(`/study/room/${roomId}?name=${encodeURIComponent(username)}&ws=${encodeURIComponent(wsUrl)}`)\n  }\n\n  const handleQuickJoin = (room: string) => {\n    const name = username.trim() || 'Học sinh ' + Math.floor(Math.random() * 100)\n    const wsProtocol = window.location.protocol === 'https:' ? 'wss:' : 'ws:'\n\n[134 more lines in file. Use offset=65 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776585535868}}
{"type":"message","id":"b6658376","parentId":"97c3160f","timestamp":"2026-04-19T07:59:09.992Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the issue - the WebSocket URL passed via query params might not work correctly because when the page loads at `/study/room/CTDL-01?name=...&ws=...`, the URL has query params and they might get lost in the redirect.\n\nAlso, the main issue is likely that the `ws` parameter is being passed correctly but the WebRTC signaling might not be fully working. Let me think about what could be wrong:\n\n1. The room page receives `wsUrl` from query params but the StudyRoom component uses it directly as `socketUrl`\n2. The WebSocket connects to `ws://host/?room=roomId&name=username`\n\n\n3. The server extracts the room and username from the query string, notifies existing peers about the new user, and sends back any existing peers to the new user\n4. When the new user receives an offer request from the server, it creates an offer and sends it back\n5. The offer gets relayed to the target peer, who then processes it\n\nWait, I need to look more carefully at the actual flow here. Looking at the server-side code, I see it's sending existing peers to the new user and broadcasting a join message to others, but I should verify the full message structure to make sure the offer exchange is actually happening.\n\nThe real issue is that the new user isn't receiving any peers to connect to yet, and when they send an offer, there's no guarantee the target peer is set up to receive it. Plus, when the first user joins an empty room, they're just getting notified about themselves joining, which isn't useful. Looking at the actual issue more carefully, the WebSocket connection itself might not be establishing properly. The room ID could be getting URL-encoded in the routing, which might be breaking the query parameter parsing when the client tries to connect. Let me trace through the exact message flow: when a peer joins, they receive an empty list of existing peers and broadcast their own entry, but the real problem is likely in how the WebSocket URL is being constructed and whether it's even reaching the server in the first place.\n\nI'm also wondering if there's a disconnect between how the old Socket.IO study page worked and the new implementation. The WebSocket server expects connections at the root path, but Socket.IO reserves `/socket.io` for its own traffic, so they shouldn't conflict. The `noServer: true` option should handle the upgrade correctly. But looking at the actual StudyRoom component, I'm noticing the video and audio toggles modify the local stream tracks, so the core media controls are actually functioning—the real problem is likely in the peer-to-peer connection establishment itself.","thinkingSignature":"4a9b6f196f43921d24368e3428baa3174046a69eb53c674b407d17ff4100bc87"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_cn1ik0e669ee_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s -o /dev/null -w \"%{http_code}\" http://localhost:3000/study && echo \"\" && curl -s -o /dev/null -w \"%{http_code}\" http://localhost:3000/study/room/test","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":0,"output":625,"cacheRead":65980,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":66605,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776585535897,"responseId":"0633be413d739cf060384dd49bf7558f"}}
