{"type":"message","id":"6bf16fa0","parentId":"92303496","timestamp":"2026-04-19T07:59:58.443Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Pages are loading. Let me check the actual content of the study room page and see if there are any issues with the component rendering.\n\nThe main problem might be that the StudyRoom component uses `useSearchParams()` which needs Suspense boundary in Next.js 14. Let me check if that's causing issues.Also, let me trace the WebRTC flow more carefully.\n\nActually, looking at the study-room.tsx code again, I see a potential issue: the `handleSignal` function in StudyRoom handles `offer-request` but in the server code, the server broadcasts `user-joined` events, not `offer-request` events. The offer flow is:\n\n\nNew user connects → server broadcasts `user-joined` → but there's no `offer-request` being triggered. I think the flow should be: when a new user joins, existing users should request an offer from them, and when someone receives a `user-joined` event, they should create and send an offer to the new user.\n\nLooking at the code, existing users don't request offers from the new user, so I need to update the server to send an `offer-request` message to the new user telling them who they need to call. But actually, the simpler approach is to have the new user initiate the offer creation themselves when they join.\n\nI'm realizing the real issue is that the WebSocket URL is being passed as a query parameter through the router, but the `ws://` protocol might not parse correctly as a URL. Let me check how the URL is being constructed and passed to the StudyRoom component. The WebSocket connection should establish on mount, and when peers receive the user-joined event, they create an offer and send it back, which gets relayed to the new user. But I'm realizing there might be an issue with how the server handles the offer-request—it sends the request to the new user, but the from field might be set to the socket ID rather than the peer's actual identifier. Actually, I think I'm overcomplicating this. Let me simplify the approach entirely.\n\nI should switch to a mesh topology where every peer connects directly to every other peer instead of relying on the server for WebRTC signaling. The server just handles room coordination and message relay, while peers exchange SDP offers and answers directly. Let me rewrite the StudyRoom component with a simpler signaling flow where the server broadcasts user-joined events with peer IDs, and each peer creates and sends an offer to every other peer.\n\nNow I'm updating the server to send proper user-joined messages with peer IDs, and rewriting the StudyRoom component to handle the connection logic more cleanly.","thinkingSignature":"26acab808a3d0c50b36ca7ba79bc69a4290ed7e960345992312e7ebc1ee7d60d"},{"type":"text","text":"Bug nằm ở WebRTC signaling flow. Cần fix toàn bộ:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_rdf6cp5m1993_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/maiy-tech-hub/components/study/study-room.tsx","content":"'use client'\n\nimport { useState, useEffect, useRef, useCallback } from 'react'\nimport { useRouter } from 'next/navigation'\nimport { VideoGrid, type VideoPeer } from './video-grid'\nimport { MediaControls } from './media-controls'\nimport { ChatPanel, type ChatMessage } from './chat-panel'\nimport { getLocalStream, getScreenStream, stopStream, toggleTrack, RTC_CONFIG } from '@/lib/webrtc'\nimport { Loader2, Wifi, WifiOff } from 'lucide-react'\n\ninterface StudyRoomProps {\n  roomId: string\n  username: string\n  socketUrl: string\n}\n\ninterface RoomPeer {\n  peerId: string\n  username: string\n  pc: RTCPeerConnection\n  stream?: MediaStream\n}\n\nexport function StudyRoom({ roomId, username, socketUrl }: StudyRoomProps) {\n  const router = useRouter()\n  const [isConnecting, setIsConnecting] = useState(true)\n  const [isConnected, setIsConnected] = useState(false)\n  const [isMicOn, setIsMicOn] = useState(false)\n  const [isCameraOn, setIsCameraOn] = useState(false)\n  const [isScreenOn, setIsScreenOn] = useState(false)\n  const [isChatOpen, setIsChatOpen] = useState(false)\n  const [messages, setMessages] = useState<ChatMessage[]>([])\n  const [unreadMessages, setUnreadMessages] = useState(0)\n  const [peers, setPeers] = useState<VideoPeer[]>([])\n  const [participantCount, setParticipantCount] = useState(1)\n  const [connectionError, setConnectionError] = useState<string | null>(null)\n\n  const localStreamRef = useRef<MediaStream | null>(null)\n  const screenStreamRef = useRef<MediaStream | null>(null)\n  const wsRef = useRef<WebSocket | null>(null)\n  const myPeerIdRef = useRef<string>('')\n  const peersRef = useRef<Map<string, RoomPeer>>(new Map())\n  const reconnectTimerRef = useRef<NodeJS.Timeout | null>(null)\n  const [localStream, setLocalStream] = useState<MediaStream | null>(null)\n\n  // ── WebSocket ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n  const connectWS = useCallback(() => {\n    if (wsRef.current?.readyState === WebSocket.OPEN) return\n\n    try {\n      const ws = new WebSocket(socketUrl)\n      wsRef.current = ws\n\n      ws.onopen = () => {\n        setIsConnecting(false)\n        setIsConnected(true)\n        setConnectionError(null)\n        // Join room\n        ws.send(JSON.stringify({ type: 'join', roomId, username }))\n      }\n\n      ws.onmessage = async (event) => {\n        try {\n          const msg = JSON.parse(event.data)\n          await handleMessage(msg)\n        } catch (e) {\n          console.error('WS message error:', e)\n        }\n      }\n\n      ws.onclose = () => {\n        setIsConnected(false)\n        // Reconnect after 3s\n        reconnectTimerRef.current = setTimeout(connectWS, 3000)\n      }\n\n      ws.onerror = () => {\n        setConnectionError('Không thể kết nối WebSocket')\n        ws.close()\n      }\n    } catch (e) {\n      setConnectionError('Lỗi kết nối: ' + String(e))\n    }\n  }, [roomId, username, socketUrl])\n\n  useEffect(() => {\n    connectWS()\n    return () => {\n      wsRef.current?.close()\n      if (reconnectTimerRef.current) clearTimeout(reconnectTimerRef.current)\n    }\n  }, [connectWS])\n\n  // ── Message handler ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n  const handleMessage = async (msg: any) => {\n    switch (msg.type) {\n      case 'welcome': {\n        // Server tells us our peer ID\n        myPeerIdRef.current = msg.peerId\n        setParticipantCount(msg.userCount || 1)\n        // Send offer to all existing peers\n        for (const peer of msg.peers || []) {\n          await createOfferTo(peer.peerId)\n        }\n        break\n      }\n\n      case 'peer-joined': {\n        // New peer joined — create offer to them\n        if (msg.peerId !== myPeerIdRef.current) {\n          setParticipantCount((n) => n + 1)\n          await createOfferTo(msg.peerId)\n        }\n        break\n      }\n\n      case 'peer-left': {\n        removePeer(msg.peerId)\n        setParticipantCount((n) => Math.max(1, n - 1))\n        break\n      }\n\n      case 'offer': {\n        await handleOffer(msg.peerId, msg.sdp)\n        break\n      }\n\n      case 'answer': {\n        await handleAnswer(msg.peerId, msg.sdp)\n        break\n      }\n\n      case 'ice-candidate': {\n        await handleIceCandidate(msg.peerId, msg.candidate)\n        break\n      }\n\n      case 'chat': {\n        const isOwn = msg.from === myPeerIdRef.current\n        if (!isOwn) {\n          setMessages((prev) => [\n            ...prev,\n            {\n              id: crypto.randomUUID(),\n              from: msg.from,\n              fromName: msg.fromName || msg.from,\n              text: msg.text,\n              timestamp: Date.now(),\n              isOwn: false,\n            },\n          ])\n          if (!isChatOpen) setUnreadMessages((n) => n + 1)\n        }\n        break\n      }\n\n      case 'room-state': {\n        setParticipantCount(msg.users?.length || 1)\n        break\n      }\n    }\n  }\n\n  // ── WebRTC ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n  const createPeerConnection = (peerId: string): RTCPeerConnection => {\n    const pc = new RTCPeerConnection(RTC_CONFIG)\n\n    pc.ontrack = (e) => {\n      const [stream] = e.streams\n      if (stream) {\n        setPeers((prev) => {\n          const existing = prev.find((p) => p.peerId === peerId)\n          if (existing) {\n            return prev.map((p) => p.peerId === peerId ? { ...p, stream } : p)\n          } else {\n            return [...prev, {\n              peerId,\n              peerName: peersRef.current.get(peerId)?.username || peerId,\n              stream,\n            }]\n          }\n        })\n      }\n    }\n\n    pc.onicecandidate = (e) => {\n      if (e.candidate) {\n        wsRef.current?.send(JSON.stringify({\n          type: 'ice-candidate',\n          peerId,\n          candidate: e.candidate.toJSON(),\n        }))\n      }\n    }\n\n    pc.onconnectionstatechange = () => {\n      if (pc.connectionState === 'failed' || pc.connectionState === 'disconnected') {\n        removePeer(peerId)\n      }\n    }\n\n    return pc\n  }\n\n  const createOfferTo = async (peerId: string) => {\n    if (!localStreamRef.current) return\n    if (peersRef.current.has(peerId)) return // Already connected\n\n    const pc = createPeerConnection(peerId)\n\n    // Add local tracks\n    localStreamRef.current.getTracks().forEach((track) => {\n      pc.addTrack(track, localStreamRef.current!)\n    })\n\n    peersRef.current.set(peerId, { peerId, username: peerId, pc })\n\n    try {\n      const offer = await pc.createOffer()\n      await pc.setLocalDescription(offer)\n      wsRef.current?.send(JSON.stringify({ type: 'offer', peerId, sdp: pc.localDescription }))\n    } catch (e) {\n      console.error('Create offer error:', e)\n      peersRef.current.delete(peerId)\n    }\n  }\n\n  const handleOffer = async (peerId: string, sdp: RTCSessionDescriptionInit) => {\n    if (!localStreamRef.current) return\n\n    const pc = createPeerConnection(peerId)\n\n    // Add local tracks\n    localStreamRef.current.getTracks().forEach((track) => {\n      pc.addTrack(track, localStreamRef.current!)\n    })\n\n    peersRef.current.set(peerId, { peerId, username: peerId, pc })\n\n    try {\n      await pc.setRemoteDescription(new RTCSessionDescription(sdp))\n      const answer = await pc.createAnswer()\n      await pc.setLocalDescription(answer)\n      wsRef.current?.send(JSON.stringify({ type: 'answer', peerId, sdp: pc.localDescription }))\n    } catch (e) {\n      console.error('Handle offer error:', e)\n    }\n  }\n\n  const handleAnswer = async (peerId: string, sdp: RTCSessionDescriptionInit) => {\n    const peer = peersRef.current.get(peerId)\n    if (peer) {\n      try {\n        await peer.pc.setRemoteDescription(new RTCSessionDescription(sdp))\n      } catch (e) {\n        console.error('Handle answer error:', e)\n      }\n    }\n  }\n\n  const handleIceCandidate = async (peerId: string, candidate: RTCIceCandidateInit) => {\n    const peer = peersRef.current.get(peerId)\n    if (peer) {\n      try {\n        await peer.pc.addIceCandidate(new RTCIceCandidate(candidate))\n      } catch (e) {\n        // Ignore\n      }\n    }\n  }\n\n  const removePeer = (peerId: string) => {\n    const peer = peersRef.current.get(peerId)\n    if (peer) {\n      peer.pc.close()\n      peersRef.current.delete(peerId)\n    }\n    setPeers((prev) => prev.filter((p) => p.peerId !== peerId))\n  }\n\n  // ── Media controls ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n  const toggleMic = () => {\n    const track = localStreamRef.current?.getAudioTracks()[0]\n    if (track) {\n      toggleTrack(track)\n      setIsMicOn(track.enabled)\n    }\n  }\n\n  const toggleCamera = () => {\n    const track = localStreamRef.current?.getVideoTracks()[0]\n    if (track) {\n      toggleTrack(track)\n      setIsCameraOn(track.enabled)\n    }\n  }\n\n  const toggleScreen = async () => {\n    if (isScreenOn) {\n      stopStream(screenStreamRef.current || undefined)\n      screenStreamRef.current = null\n      setIsScreenOn(false)\n      wsRef.current?.send(JSON.stringify({ type: 'screen-share', sharing: false }))\n    } else {\n      const stream = await getScreenStream()\n      if (!stream) return\n\n      screenStreamRef.current = stream\n      setIsScreenOn(true)\n\n      // Replace video track in all peer connections\n      const videoTrack = stream.getVideoTracks()[0]\n      peersRef.current.forEach((peer) => {\n        const sender = peer.pc.getSenders().find((s) => s.track?.kind === 'video')\n        if (sender) {\n          sender.replaceTrack(videoTrack)\n        } else {\n          peer.pc.addTrack(videoTrack, stream)\n        }\n      })\n\n      wsRef.current?.send(JSON.stringify({ type: 'screen-share', sharing: true }))\n\n      videoTrack.onended = () => {\n        stopStream(screenStreamRef.current || undefined)\n        screenStreamRef.current = null\n        setIsScreenOn(false)\n        wsRef.current?.send(JSON.stringify({ type: 'screen-share', sharing: false }))\n      }\n    }\n  }\n\n  // ── Chat ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n  const sendMessage = (text: string) => {\n    wsRef.current?.send(JSON.stringify({ type: 'chat', text }))\n    setMessages((prev) => [\n      ...prev,\n      { id: crypto.randomUUID(), from: 'local', fromName: username, text, timestamp: Date.now(), isOwn: true },\n    ])\n  }\n\n  // ── Init media ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n  useEffect(() => {\n    const startMedia = async () => {\n      try {\n        const stream = await getLocalStream(true, true)\n        if (stream) {\n          localStreamRef.current = stream\n          setLocalStream(stream.clone())\n          setIsMicOn(true)\n          setIsCameraOn(true)\n        }\n      } catch (e) {\n        console.warn('Could not get media:', e)\n        // Start with no media — user can enable later\n        try {\n          const videoOff = await navigator.mediaDevices.getUserMedia({ video: false, audio: true })\n          localStreamRef.current = videoOff\n          setLocalStream(videoOff)\n          setIsMicOn(true)\n        } catch {\n          // No media at all\n        }\n      }\n    }\n    startMedia()\n\n    return () => {\n      stopStream(localStreamRef.current || undefined)\n      stopStream(screenStreamRef.current || undefined)\n      peersRef.current.forEach((p) => p.pc.close())\n      peersRef.current.clear()\n    }\n  }, [])\n\n  // ── Leave ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n  const handleLeave = () => {\n    wsRef.current?.close()\n    stopStream(localStreamRef.current || undefined)\n    stopStream(screenStreamRef.current || undefined)\n    peersRef.current.forEach((p) => p.pc.close())\n    peersRef.current.clear()\n    router.push('/study')\n  }\n\n  return (\n    <div className=\"flex flex-col h-[calc(100vh-4rem)]\">\n      {/* Status */}\n      <div className=\"flex items-center justify-between px-4 py-2 bg-muted/50 border-b border-border text-xs\">\n        <div className=\"flex items-center gap-3\">\n          <span className=\"font-medium\">Phòng: {roomId}</span>\n          <span className=\"text-muted-foreground\">{participantCount} người</span>\n          {myPeerIdRef.current && (\n            <span className=\"text-muted-foreground/50 font-mono text-[10px]\">\n              ID: {myPeerIdRef.current.slice(0, 8)}\n            </span>\n          )}\n        </div>\n        <div className=\"flex items-center gap-2\">\n          {connectionError ? (\n            <span className=\"text-red-500 text-xs\">{connectionError}</span>\n          ) : isConnected ? (\n            <>\n              <Wifi className=\"h-3 w-3 text-green-500\" />\n              <span className=\"text-green-500\">Kết nối</span>\n            </>\n          ) : (\n            <>\n              <WifiOff className=\"h-3 w-3 text-red-500\" />\n              <span className=\"text-red-500\">{isConnecting ? 'Đang kết nối...' : 'Mất kết nối'}</span>\n            </>\n          )}\n        </div>\n      </div>\n\n      {/* Content */}\n      {isConnecting ? (\n        <div className=\"flex-1 flex items-center justify-center\">\n          <div className=\"flex flex-col items-center gap-3\">\n            <Loader2 className=\"h-8 w-8 animate-spin text-primary\" />\n            <p className=\"text-muted-foreground\">Đang kết nối phòng học...</p>\n            {connectionError && (\n              <p className=\"text-red-500 text-sm\">{connectionError}</p>\n            )}\n          </div>\n        </div>\n      ) : (\n        <>\n          {/* Debug info */}\n          {process.env.NODE_ENV === 'development' && (\n            <div className=\"bg-amber-500/10 border-b border-amber-500/30 px-4 py-1 text-xs text-amber-600\">\n              WebRTC: {peers.length} peers | Local: {isMicOn ? '🎤' : '🔇'} {isCameraOn ? '📹' : '📷'}\n            </div>\n          )}\n\n          <div className=\"flex-1 overflow-y-auto bg-slate-950/50\">\n            <VideoGrid\n              localStream={localStream}\n              peers={peers}\n              onSelectPeer={(id) => console.log('select', id)}\n            />\n          </div>\n        </>\n      )}\n\n      {/* Controls */}\n      <div className=\"border-t border-border bg-background\">\n        <MediaControls\n          isMicOn={isMicOn}\n          isCameraOn={isCameraOn}\n          isScreenOn={isScreenOn}\n          unreadMessages={unreadMessages}\n          participantCount={participantCount}\n          onToggleMic={toggleMic}\n          onToggleCamera={toggleCamera}\n          onToggleScreen={toggleScreen}\n          onToggleChat={() => {\n            setIsChatOpen(!isChatOpen)\n            if (!isChatOpen) setUnreadMessages(0)\n          }}\n          onLeave={handleLeave}\n        />\n      </div>\n\n      <ChatPanel\n        messages={messages}\n        onSend={sendMessage}\n        username={username}\n        isOpen={isChatOpen}\n        onClose={() => setIsChatOpen(false)}\n      />\n    </div>\n  )\n}\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":81,"output":4264,"cacheRead":65436,"cacheWrite":1107,"totalTokens":70888,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776585550679,"responseId":"0633be50799f2147d0e5706949cba82a"}}
