{"type":"message","id":"422e0ce2","parentId":"5c0659a7","timestamp":"2026-04-19T08:00:29.798Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me also add `uuid` to the dependencies since the study page uses `uuidv4`. Let me also update the study page to not use `uuid` since we can use `crypto.randomUUID()` instead (which is available in modern browsers and Node.js).\n\nAlso, I need to update the study page to ensure the WebSocket URL is passed correctly. The current implementation passes `ws://host` as a query param which might cause issues. Let me simplify by using the same host.\n\nActually, wait - there's another issue. The study page passes the `ws` URL as a query parameter. When navigating from `/study` to `/study/room/CTDL-01?name=...&ws=...`, the router should preserve the query params. \n\nBut since we're using a client-side router.push, the query params should be included. Let me check the actual flow: the user fills in their name and room ID on the study page, then clicks the button to navigate to the room page with the WebSocket URL as a query parameter. The room page reads these params and passes them to the StudyRoom component. The WebSocket connects to `ws://${window.location.host}` which resolves to `ws://103.253.21.`, and then the server handles the upgrade from there.\n\nNow I'm realizing the issue might be with how the query parameters are being encoded and decoded. The URL parameter should preserve the `ws://` protocol, but I need to verify that `window.location.host` is correctly populated in the production VPS environment to ensure the WebSocket connection string is being constructed properly.\n\nLet me also make sure the build passes and double-check that `crypto.randomUUID()` is available since we're targeting modern browsers and Node.js 18+.","thinkingSignature":"950ba72c8f591c459bcad35a11c0605deeaca55936f2abd5c4b27d8da6281e4a"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_qir2aieu8eif_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/maiy-tech-hub && yarn build 2>&1 | grep -E \"Type error|✓|Failed|pages\" | head -10","yieldMs":50000,"timeout":120}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":108,"output":447,"cacheRead":66557,"cacheWrite":6025,"totalTokens":73137,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776585619357,"responseId":"0633be9425096e043b387abd8e3886b4"}}
