{"type":"message","id":"d9a636ba","parentId":"628dc94b","timestamp":"2026-04-19T08:06:34.274Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Ah, the local server IS also returning 404 for `_next/static/chunks/main-app.js`. This is strange because the page returns 200. But the HTML references the correct paths with `?v=` query strings.\n\nActually wait - `main-app.js` returns 404 but `main-app.js?v=...` would work. The HTML has `main-app.js?v=1776585985278`. So the issue is that the browser is requesting without the version parameter, but our curl request also had no version param and got 404.\n\nHmm, actually looking more carefully - the HTML shows `_next/static/chunks/main-app.js?v=1776585985278` and when I request that exact URL it works (because the server ignores query params for static files). But without the `?v=` it returns 404.\n\n\nSo the real problem is the static file handler isn't matching these chunk files without the version parameter. I need to check the Next.js configuration to see why the build isn't generating the proper static file mappings.","thinkingSignature":"59898a31169874c07bf1660de5a8f33e1f4f302ca54f9fb966d705275ed247ee"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_0swb3ki2wdo3_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s \"http://localhost:3000/_next/static/chunks/main-app.js?v=1776585985278\" -o /dev/null -w \"%{http_code}\" && echo \" with version param\"","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":144,"output":288,"cacheRead":74730,"cacheWrite":1239,"totalTokens":76401,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776585985389,"responseId":"0633c002e685441fa45bed99889cf486"}}
