{"type":"message","id":"44a328a4","parentId":"9069435d","timestamp":"2026-04-19T08:08:52.330Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to think about the WebSocket server issue. Vercel doesn't support custom WebSocket servers directly (they have their own `socket.io` support through serverless functions or their serverless websocket support). But Vercel does support WebSocket through their Edge Functions or by using their serverless WebSocket support.For WebRTC signaling, we need WebSocket. On Vercel, we can use:\n1. Vercel's native WebSocket support (serverless)\n2. Third-party WebSocket services like Pusher, Ably, or PeerJS\n\nActually, the best approach for WebRTC on Vercel is to use a free STUN/TURN server and PeerJS (which handles signaling via their free server), OR use a free WebSocket relay service.\n\n\nI'll start with PeerJS since it provides free WebRTC signaling out of the box. For the study room, the WebSocket just handles signaling—the actual video/audio flows through WebRTC peer-to-peer connections, so we mainly need to relay those signaling messages. I could use a free PeerJS server or deploy our own signaling server to Railway for free tier support.\n\nSetting up PeerJS...","thinkingSignature":"1a0a44e2cb234218759e66dfbeeb3776b919f202f6183941ed160a6444b69706"},{"type":"text","text":"Cần chuyển sang **PeerJS** cho WebRTC signaling — miễn phí, không cần server riêng:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_hl664177isad_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/maiy-tech-hub && yarn add peerjs 2>&1 | tail -3","timeout":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":108,"output":334,"cacheRead":78415,"cacheWrite":823,"totalTokens":79680,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776586123429,"responseId":"0633c08c96be27646333e72d13faaae4"}}
{"type":"message","id":"fb97fa3a","parentId":"44a328a4","timestamp":"2026-04-19T08:09:01.353Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_hl664177isad_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"├─ sdp@3.2.2\n└─ webrtc-adapter@9.0.5\nDone in 8.56s."}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":8958,"aggregated":"├─ sdp@3.2.2\n└─ webrtc-adapter@9.0.5\nDone in 8.56s.","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776586141322}}
{"type":"message","id":"026f31b9","parentId":"fb97fa3a","timestamp":"2026-04-19T08:09:41.295Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me update the study-room component to use PeerJS instead of the custom WebSocket signaling.","thinkingSignature":"5cbd9ce938208f6ff15db7a659437d86f08cf498f9faa682724264fe57046333"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_i6vx7vp6baq6_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/maiy-tech-hub/components/study/study-room.tsx","content":"'use client'\n\nimport { useState, useEffect, useRef, useCallback } from 'react'\nimport { useRouter } from 'next/navigation'\nimport Peer, { MediaConnection, DataConnection } from 'peerjs'\nimport { VideoGrid, type VideoPeer } from './video-grid'\nimport { MediaControls } from './media-controls'\nimport { ChatPanel, type ChatMessage } from './chat-panel'\nimport { getLocalStream, getScreenStream, stopStream, toggleTrack, RTC_CONFIG } from '@/lib/webrtc'\nimport { Loader2, Wifi, WifiOff } from 'lucide-react'\n\ninterface StudyRoomProps {\n  roomId: string\n  username: string\n  socketUrl: string\n}\n\ninterface ConnectedPeer {\n  peerId: string\n  username: string\n  mediaConn?: MediaConnection\n  dataConn?: DataConnection\n  stream?: MediaStream\n}\n\nexport function StudyRoom({ roomId, username }: StudyRoomProps) {\n  const router = useRouter()\n  const [isConnecting, setIsConnecting] = useState(true)\n  const [isConnected, setIsConnected] = useState(false)\n  const [isMicOn, setIsMicOn] = useState(false)\n  const [isCameraOn, setIsCameraOn] = useState(false)\n  const [isScreenOn, setIsScreenOn] = useState(false)\n  const [isChatOpen, setIsChatOpen] = useState(false)\n  const [messages, setMessages] = useState<ChatMessage[]>([])\n  const [unreadMessages, setUnreadMessages] = useState(0)\n  const [peers, setPeers] = useState<VideoPeer[]>([])\n  const [participantCount, setParticipantCount] = useState(1)\n  const [error, setError] = useState<string | null>(null)\n\n  const peerRef = useRef<Peer | null>(null)\n  const myPeerIdRef = useRef<string>('')\n  const localStreamRef = useRef<MediaStream | null>(null)\n  const screenStreamRef = useRef<MediaStream | null>(null)\n  const peersRef = useRef<Map<string, ConnectedPeer>>(new Map())\n  const [localStream, setLocalStream] = useState<MediaStream | null>(null)\n\n  // ── Init PeerJS ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n  useEffect(() => {\n    const initPeer = () => {\n      // Use free PeerJS cloud server — no server needed\n      const peer = new Peer(`maiy-${roomId}-${Date.now()}-${Math.random().toString(36).slice(2, 8)}`, {\n        host: '0.peerjs.com',\n        port: 443,\n        secure: true,\n        path: '/',\n        config: {\n          iceServers: RTC_CONFIG.iceServers!,\n        },\n      })\n\n      peer.on('open', (id) => {\n        myPeerIdRef.current = id\n        setIsConnecting(false)\n        setIsConnected(true)\n        // Announce to signaling room\n        broadcastToRoom('join', { peerId: id, username })\n      })\n\n      peer.on('connection', (conn) => {\n        handleDataConnection(conn)\n      })\n\n      peer.on('call', (call) => {\n        handleMediaCall(call)\n      })\n\n      peer.on('error', (err) => {\n        console.error('PeerJS error:', err)\n        if (err.type === 'peer-unavailable') {\n          // Peer left or room empty — ignore\n        } else {\n          setError(`Lỗi kết nối: ${err.message}`)\n        }\n      })\n\n      peer.on('disconnected', () => {\n        setIsConnected(false)\n        // Try to reconnect\n        setTimeout(() => peer.reconnect(), 3000)\n      })\n\n      peerRef.current = peer\n    }\n\n    initPeer()\n\n    return () => {\n      peerRef.current?.destroy()\n    }\n  }, [roomId, username])\n\n  // ── Handle incoming data connection ─────────────────────────────────────────\n  const handleDataConnection = (conn: DataConnection) => {\n    conn.on('open', () => {\n      // Send our info\n      conn.send({ type: 'info', username })\n    })\n\n    conn.on('data', (data: any) => {\n      handlePeerData(conn.peer, data)\n    })\n\n    conn.on('close', () => {\n      removePeer(conn.peer)\n    })\n  }\n\n  // ── Handle incoming media call ──────────────────────────────────────────────\n  const handleMediaCall = (call: MediaConnection) => {\n    if (!localStreamRef.current) return\n\n    // Answer with our stream\n    call.answer(localStreamRef.current)\n\n    call.on('stream', (remoteStream) => {\n      const username = peersRef.current.get(call.peer)?.username || call.peer\n      addPeerStream(call.peer, username, remoteStream)\n    })\n\n    call.on('close', () => {\n      removePeer(call.peer)\n    })\n  }\n\n  // ── Handle peer data messages ───────────────────────────────────────────────\n  const handlePeerData = (peerId: string, data: any) => {\n    switch (data.type) {\n      case 'info': {\n        // New peer identified themselves\n        const existing = peersRef.current.get(peerId)\n        if (existing) existing.username = data.username\n        setParticipantCount((n) => Math.max(n, peersRef.current.size + 1))\n        // Connect back and call them\n        connectToPeer(peerId, data.username)\n        break\n      }\n\n      case 'join': {\n        // A peer wants to connect\n        if (peerId !== myPeerIdRef.current) {\n          connectToPeer(data.peerId, data.username)\n        }\n        break\n      }\n\n      case 'leave': {\n        removePeer(data.peerId)\n        break\n      }\n\n      case 'chat': {\n        setMessages((prev) => [\n          ...prev,\n          {\n            id: crypto.randomUUID(),\n            from: peerId,\n            fromName: peersRef.current.get(peerId)?.username || peerId,\n            text: data.text,\n            timestamp: Date.now(),\n            isOwn: false,\n          },\n        ])\n        if (!isChatOpen) setUnreadMessages((n) => n + 1)\n        break\n      }\n\n      case 'screen-share': {\n        setPeers((prev) =>\n          prev.map((p) =>\n            p.peerId === peerId ? { ...p, isScreenSharing: data.sharing } : p\n          )\n        )\n        break\n      }\n    }\n  }\n\n  // ── Connect to a peer ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n  const connectToPeer = (peerId: string, peerUsername: string) => {\n    if (!peerRef.current || peersRef.current.has(peerId)) return\n    if (peerId === myPeerIdRef.current) return\n\n    const conn = peerRef.current.connect(peerId, {\n      reliable: true,\n      serialization: 'json',\n    })\n\n    conn.on('open', () => {\n      peersRef.current.set(peerId, { peerId, username: peerUsername, dataConn: conn })\n      // Send our info\n      conn.send({ type: 'info', username })\n      setParticipantCount(peersRef.current.size + 1)\n\n      // Call them with our stream\n      if (localStreamRef.current) {\n        const call = peerRef.current!.call(peerId, localStreamRef.current)\n        if (call) {\n          call.on('stream', (remoteStream) => {\n            addPeerStream(peerId, peerUsername, remoteStream)\n          })\n          call.on('close', () => removePeer(peerId))\n          peersRef.current.get(peerId)!.mediaConn = call\n        }\n      }\n    })\n\n    conn.on('data', (data: any) => {\n      handlePeerData(peerId, data)\n    })\n\n    conn.on('close', () => {\n      removePeer(peerId)\n    })\n\n    conn.on('error', () => {\n      removePeer(peerId)\n    })\n  }\n\n  // ── Broadcast to room peers ────────────────────────────────────────────────\n  const broadcastToRoom = (type: string, data: any) => {\n    peersRef.current.forEach((peer) => {\n      peer.dataConn?.send({ type, ...data })\n    })\n  }\n\n  // ── Add/update peer stream ──────────────────────────────────────────────────\n  const addPeerStream = (peerId: string, peerUsername: string, stream: MediaStream) => {\n    setPeers((prev) => {\n      const existing = prev.find((p) => p.peerId === peerId)\n      if (existing) {\n        return prev.map((p) => p.peerId === peerId ? { ...p, stream } : p)\n      } else {\n        return [...prev, { peerId, peerName: peerUsername, stream }]\n      }\n    })\n  }\n\n  // ── Remove peer ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n  const removePeer = (peerId: string) => {\n    const peer = peersRef.current.get(peerId)\n    if (peer) {\n      peer.mediaConn?.close()\n      peer.dataConn?.close()\n      peersRef.current.delete(peerId)\n    }\n    setPeers((prev) => prev.filter((p) => p.peerId !== peerId))\n    setParticipantCount(Math.max(1, peersRef.current.size + 1))\n  }\n\n  // ── Media controls ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n  const toggleMic = () => {\n    const track = localStreamRef.current?.getAudioTracks()[0]\n    if (track) {\n      toggleTrack(track)\n      setIsMicOn(track.enabled)\n    }\n  }\n\n  const toggleCamera = () => {\n    const track = localStreamRef.current?.getVideoTracks()[0]\n    if (track) {\n      toggleTrack(track)\n      setIsCameraOn(track.enabled)\n    }\n  }\n\n  const toggleScreen = async () => {\n    if (isScreenOn) {\n      stopStream(screenStreamRef.current || undefined)\n      screenStreamRef.current = null\n      setIsScreenOn(false)\n      broadcastToRoom('screen-share', { sharing: false })\n    } else {\n      const stream = await getScreenStream()\n      if (!stream) return\n\n      screenStreamRef.current = stream\n      setIsScreenOn(true)\n      broadcastToRoom('screen-share', { sharing: true })\n\n      // Replace video track in all calls\n      const videoTrack = stream.getVideoTracks()[0]\n      peersRef.current.forEach((peer) => {\n        peer.mediaConn?.peerConnection\n          ?.getSenders()\n          .find((s: any) => s.track?.kind === 'video')\n          ?.replaceTrack(videoTrack)\n      })\n\n      videoTrack.onended = () => {\n        stopStream(screenStreamRef.current || undefined)\n        screenStreamRef.current = null\n        setIsScreenOn(false)\n        broadcastToRoom('screen-share', { sharing: false })\n      }\n    }\n  }\n\n  // ── Chat ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n  const sendMessage = (text: string) => {\n    broadcastToRoom('chat', { text })\n    setMessages((prev) => [\n      ...prev,\n      { id: crypto.randomUUID(), from: 'local', fromName: username, text, timestamp: Date.now(), isOwn: true },\n    ])\n  }\n\n  // ── Init media ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n  useEffect(() => {\n    const startMedia = async () => {\n      try {\n        const stream = await getLocalStream(true, true)\n        if (stream) {\n          localStreamRef.current = stream\n          setLocalStream(stream.clone())\n          setIsMicOn(true)\n          setIsCameraOn(true)\n        }\n      } catch {\n        try {\n          const audioOnly = await navigator.mediaDevices.getUserMedia({ video: false, audio: true })\n          localStreamRef.current = audioOnly\n          setLocalStream(audioOnly)\n          setIsMicOn(true)\n        } catch {\n          // No media\n        }\n      }\n    }\n    startMedia()\n\n    return () => {\n      stopStream(localStreamRef.current || undefined)\n      stopStream(screenStreamRef.current || undefined)\n    }\n  }, [])\n\n  // ── Leave ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n  const handleLeave = () => {\n    broadcastToRoom('leave', { peerId: myPeerIdRef.current })\n    peerRef.current?.destroy()\n    stopStream(localStreamRef.current || undefined)\n    stopStream(screenStreamRef.current || undefined)\n    router.push('/study')\n  }\n\n  return (\n    <div className=\"flex flex-col h-[calc(100vh-4rem)]\">\n      {/* Status */}\n      <div className=\"flex items-center justify-between px-4 py-2 bg-muted/50 border-b border-border text-xs\">\n        <div className=\"flex items-center gap-3\">\n          <span className=\"font-medium\">Phòng: {roomId}</span>\n          <span className=\"text-muted-foreground\">{participantCount} người</span>\n          {myPeerIdRef.current && (\n            <span className=\"text-muted-foreground/50 font-mono text-[10px]\">\n              {myPeerIdRef.current.slice(0, 12)}...\n            </span>\n          )}\n        </div>\n        <div className=\"flex items-center gap-2\">\n          {error ? (\n            <span className=\"text-red-500 text-xs\">{error}</span>\n          ) : isConnected ? (\n            <>\n              <Wifi className=\"h-3 w-3 text-green-500\" />\n              <span className=\"text-green-500\">PeerJS connected</span>\n            </>\n          ) : (\n            <>\n              <WifiOff className=\"h-3 w-3 text-red-500\" />\n              <span className=\"text-red-500\">{isConnecting ? 'Đang kết nối...' : 'Mất kết nối'}</span>\n            </>\n          )}\n        </div>\n      </div>\n\n      {/* Connecting */}\n      {isConnecting && (\n        <div className=\"flex-1 flex items-center justify-center\">\n          <div className=\"flex flex-col items-center gap-3\">\n            <Loader2 className=\"h-8 w-8 animate-spin text-primary\" />\n            <p className=\"text-muted-foreground\">Đang kết nối qua PeerJS...</p>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n      )}\n\n      {/* Video grid */}\n      {!isConnecting && (\n        <div className=\"flex-1 overflow-y-auto bg-slate-950/50\">\n          <VideoGrid\n            localStream={localStream}\n            peers={peers}\n            onSelectPeer={() => {}}\n          />\n        </div>\n      )}\n\n      {/* Controls */}\n      <div className=\"border-t border-border bg-background\">\n        <MediaControls\n          isMicOn={isMicOn}\n          isCameraOn={isCameraOn}\n          isScreenOn={isScreenOn}\n          unreadMessages={unreadMessages}\n          participantCount={participantCount}\n          onToggleMic={toggleMic}\n          onToggleCamera={toggleCamera}\n          onToggleScreen={toggleScreen}\n          onToggleChat={() => {\n            setIsChatOpen(!isChatOpen)\n            if (!isChatOpen) setUnreadMessages(0)\n          }}\n          onLeave={handleLeave}\n        />\n      </div>\n\n      <ChatPanel\n        messages={messages}\n        onSend={sendMessage}\n        username={username}\n        isOpen={isChatOpen}\n        onClose={() => setIsChatOpen(false)}\n      />\n    </div>\n  )\n}\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":110,"output":3426,"cacheRead":78776,"cacheWrite":842,"totalTokens":83154,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776586141374,"responseId":"0633c09f5f40eab44c0e6be066f1af31"}}
