{"type":"message","id":"abd89427","parentId":"25789070","timestamp":"2026-04-19T08:11:14.609Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_3hezrgmfo336_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import { MetadataRoute } from 'next'\nimport { getAllArticles } from '@/lib/content'\nimport { CATEGORIES, SITE } from '@/config/site'\n\nexport default async function sitemap(): Promise<MetadataRoute.Sitemap> {\n  const articles = await getAllArticles()\n\n  const articleUrls = articles.map((article) => ({\n    url: `${SITE.url}/articles/${article.slug}`,\n    lastModified: new Date(article.publishedAt),\n    changeFrequency: 'monthly' as const,\n    priority: 0.8,\n  }))\n\n  const categoryUrls = CATEGORIES.map((cat) => ({\n    url: `${SITE.url}/articles/category/${cat.slug}`,\n    lastModified: new Date(),\n    changeFrequency: 'weekly' as const,\n    priority: 0.7,\n  }))\n\n  return [\n    {\n      url: SITE.url,\n      lastModified: new Date(),\n      changeFrequency: 'daily',\n      priority: 1,\n    },\n    {\n      url: `${SITE.url}/articles`,\n      lastModified: new Date(),\n      changeFrequency: 'daily',\n      priority: 0.9,\n    },\n    {\n      url: `${SITE.url}/music`,\n      lastModified: new Date(),\n      changeFrequency: 'monthly',\n      priority: 0.6,\n    },\n    {\n      url: `${SITE.url}/study`,\n      lastModified: new Date(),\n      changeFrequency: 'monthly',\n      priority: 0.6,\n    },\n    {\n      url: `${SITE.url}/about`,\n      lastModified: new Date(),\n      changeFrequency: 'yearly',\n      priority: 0.5,\n    },\n    ...categoryUrls,\n    ...articleUrls,\n  ]\n}\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776586274590}}
{"type":"message","id":"ddff82a9","parentId":"abd89427","timestamp":"2026-04-19T08:11:25.801Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The sitemap is calling `getAllArticles()` which should return all articles. But it's looking for the file at `content/articles/linear-regression-python.mdx` (root level). Let me check the sitemap again...\n\nThe issue is that the sitemap is being pre-rendered at build time. At that point, `getAllArticles()` should return all articles correctly (since we fixed `getArticleFiles` to recursively find all MDX files). But the error says it's looking for the file at `content/articles/linear-regression-python.mdx` (no subdirectory).\n\nWait, actually the build error says it's looking for `content/articles/linear-regression-python.mdx` at the ROOT level, not in the `ai/` subdirectory. \n\nI need to verify what `getAllArticles()` is actually returning during the build process. The sitemap is calling this function to generate article URLs, so if the slugs don't include the subdirectory path, the URLs will be wrong. Let me trace through `getArticleFiles()` to see what slugs are being generated—it should be recursively walking through all the subdirectories and building slugs that include the full path like `ai/linear-regression-python`.\n\nActually, I'm realizing the issue now: when `getArticleFiles()` returns filenames only without the subdirectory path, the slug becomes just `linear-regression-python`, which means the sitemap generates a URL like `/articles/linear-regression-python`. But then `getArticleBySlug()` tries to find the file by searching recursively for `linear-regression-python.mdx`, and since there are multiple articles with that slug across different categories, it returns the first one it finds—which happens to be the wrong one.\n\nWait, but that would cause a different error than what I'm seeing. The real problem is that during the build, `getAllArticles()` is failing because it can't find `content/articles/linear-regression-python.mdx` at the root level. Let me trace through the code to see where this root-level path is coming from.","thinkingSignature":"99a9b9f26eb46f12e9d34d06b445ac7df6be9ef3d4afcad0d5b44b8b26f603b4"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_oy732l01co6o_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/maiy-tech-hub/lib/content.ts","limit":55}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":441,"output":471,"cacheRead":83849,"cacheWrite":451,"totalTokens":85212,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776586274626,"responseId":"0633c1244f8acdb559a5842797fcba51"}}
{"type":"message","id":"f89b395b","parentId":"ddff82a9","timestamp":"2026-04-19T08:11:25.856Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_oy732l01co6o_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import fs from 'fs'\nimport path from 'path'\nimport matter from 'gray-matter'\nimport readingTime from 'reading-time'\nimport type { ArticleSummary } from '@/components/blog/article-card'\n\nconst CONTENT_DIR = path.join(process.cwd(), 'content', 'articles')\n\nexport interface Article extends ArticleSummary {\n  content: string\n}\n\nfunction getArticleFiles(): string[] {\n  if (!fs.existsSync(CONTENT_DIR)) return []\n  const files: string[] = []\n  function walk(dir: string) {\n    const entries = fs.readdirSync(dir, { withFileTypes: true })\n    for (const entry of entries) {\n      const full = path.join(dir, entry.name)\n      if (entry.isDirectory()) {\n        walk(full)\n      } else if (entry.name.endsWith('.mdx') || entry.name.endsWith('.md')) {\n        // Store as relative path from CONTENT_DIR, but slug = filename only (no subdirectory)\n        files.push(entry.name)\n      }\n    }\n  }\n  walk(CONTENT_DIR)\n  return files\n}\n\nexport async function getAllArticles(): Promise<ArticleSummary[]> {\n  const files = getArticleFiles()\n  const articles = files.map((file) => {\n    const slug = file.replace(/\\.(mdx|md)$/, '')\n    const raw = fs.readFileSync(path.join(CONTENT_DIR, file), 'utf-8')\n    const { data, content } = matter(raw)\n    const rt = readingTime(content)\n\n    return {\n      slug,\n      title: data.title || slug,\n      excerpt: data.excerpt || '',\n      category: data.category || 'cs-fundamentals',\n      tags: data.tags || [],\n      hero: data.hero || null,\n      author: data.author || 'MAIY Tech Hub',\n      readingTime: Math.ceil(rt.minutes),\n      publishedAt: data.date || new Date().toISOString(),\n    } as ArticleSummary\n  })\n\n  return articles.sort(\n    (a, b) => new Date(b.publishedAt).getTime() - new Date(a.publishedAt).getTime()\n  )\n\n[62 more lines in file. Use offset=56 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776586285833}}
{"type":"message","id":"8f94b3e8","parentId":"f89b395b","timestamp":"2026-04-19T08:11:34.918Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Found the bug! In `getAllArticles()`:\n```ts\nconst raw = fs.readFileSync(path.join(CONTENT_DIR, file), 'utf-8')\n```It's joining `CONTENT_DIR` with just the filename (e.g., `linear-regression-python.mdx`), which resolves to `content/articles/linear-regression-python.mdx` (root level). But the actual file is at `content/articles/ai/linear-regression-python.mdx`.\n\nI need to either:\n1. Store the full relative path in `getArticleFiles()`, OR\n2. Search for the file in subdirectories when reading in `getAllArticles()`","thinkingSignature":"7c30dddbb5839b7bcce2f5ff1396a6aa9fb91a2937f5dea509fb8b1841b184a3"},{"type":"text","text":"Found it! `getAllArticles()` đang tìm sai path — fix ngay:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_177hj9t14unh_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/maiy-tech-hub/lib/content.ts","edits":[{"oldText":"function getArticleFiles(): string[] {\n  if (!fs.existsSync(CONTENT_DIR)) return []\n  const files: string[] = []\n  function walk(dir: string) {\n    const entries = fs.readdirSync(dir, { withFileTypes: true })\n    for (const entry of entries) {\n      const full = path.join(dir, entry.name)\n      if (entry.isDirectory()) {\n        walk(full)\n      } else if (entry.name.endsWith('.mdx') || entry.name.endsWith('.md')) {\n        // Store as relative path from CONTENT_DIR, but slug = filename only (no subdirectory)\n        files.push(entry.name)\n      }\n    }\n  }\n  walk(CONTENT_DIR)\n  return files\n}","newText":"function getArticleFiles(): string[] {\n  if (!fs.existsSync(CONTENT_DIR)) return []\n  const files: string[] = []\n  function walk(dir: string) {\n    const entries = fs.readdirSync(dir, { withFileTypes: true })\n    for (const entry of entries) {\n      const full = path.join(dir, entry.name)\n      if (entry.isDirectory()) {\n        walk(full)\n      } else if (entry.name.endsWith('.mdx') || entry.name.endsWith('.md')) {\n        // Store as relative path from CONTENT_DIR (e.g. 'ai/linear-regression-python.mdx')\n        files.push(path.relative(CONTENT_DIR, full))\n      }\n    }\n  }\n  walk(CONTENT_DIR)\n  return files\n}"}]}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":527,"output":574,"cacheRead":84217,"cacheWrite":933,"totalTokens":86251,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776586285870,"responseId":"0633c12f9666d2ef2912f9613ac62cab"}}
