{"type":"message","id":"e3885e21","parentId":"174d7c00","timestamp":"2026-04-19T08:11:45.622Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now `getArticleFiles()` returns full relative paths like `ai/linear-regression-python.mdx`. And `getAllArticles()` will use `path.join(CONTENT_DIR, file)` which will correctly find the file. And the slug will be `ai/linear-regression-python`, which is wrong for the URL.\n\nWait, but I changed `getArticleFiles` to return the relative path. This means:\n- `file` = `ai/linear-regression-python.mdx`\n- `slug` = `ai/linear-regression-python`\n- `path.join(CONTENT_DIR, file)` = `content/articles/ai/linear-regression-python.mdx` ✓\n\n\n- The URL becomes `/articles/ai/linear-regression-python` ❌\n\nSo I'm back to the same problem. I need to figure out the right approach here. The URL should just be `/articles/linear-regression-python`, but I need the file path to find the content. Option 1 would be to strip the subdirectory from the slug, but then when `getArticleBySlug` tries to locate the file, it won't know where to look since there could be multiple files with the same name across different categories.\n\nThe cleanest solution is to keep the full relative path as the file identifier internally, but extract just the filename for the slug. That way `getArticleBySlug` can search through subdirectories to find the right file, and the URL stays clean without category prefixes.","thinkingSignature":"fc1e0d41582fb40ccef17e253a67ce055e7d8149e31e201aff948c27cc16b1ba"},{"type":"text","text":"Cần tách slug ra khỏi file path để URL đúng:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_rdecsgz0ywr6_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/maiy-tech-hub/lib/content.ts","edits":[{"oldText":"  const articles = files.map((file) => {\n    const slug = file.replace(/\\.(mdx|md)$/, '')\n    const raw = fs.readFileSync(path.join(CONTENT_DIR, file), 'utf-8')","newText":"  const articles = files.map((file) => {\n    // slug = filename only (no subdirectory), used for URL\n    const slug = file.replace(/\\.(mdx|md)$/, '').split('/').pop() || file\n    // fullPath includes subdirectory for file reading\n    const fullPath = path.join(CONTENT_DIR, file)\n    const raw = fs.readFileSync(fullPath, 'utf-8')"}]}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":109,"output":536,"cacheRead":84674,"cacheWrite":1515,"totalTokens":86834,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776586295033,"responseId":"0633c13882582b9a22491893c5651452"}}
