{"type":"message","id":"979221ef","parentId":"4473deab","timestamp":"2026-04-19T08:24:09.233Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to update the MDX rendering to use shiki for syntax highlighting. The issue is that shiki works asynchronously. For MDX with next-mdx-remote/rsc, I can use the `compileMDX` function from `next-mdx-remote/rsc` which supports async components. Or I can pre-process the MDX content to highlight code blocks before rendering.\n\nActually, a better approach for Next.js App Router is to use `rehype-shiki` plugin with `remark-rehype`. But that would require restructuring the MDX setup.\n\nThe simplest approach: create a server-side code highlighting component. Let me create a `HighlightedCode` component that uses shiki.\n\n\nI should update the MDXContent component to use the shiki highlighter for code blocks. Since `next-mdx-remote/rsc` supports async components, I can leverage that to handle the asynchronous highlighting directly within the component.\n\nActually, I'll pre-process the MDX at the server level instead—extracting code blocks and highlighting them before passing the content to MDXRemote.","thinkingSignature":"f253d41baadd323d0db627d8d89cea7b18972558106d70dc06185f46f9883a47"},{"type":"text","text":"Now update MDX rendering with shiki:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_0goard29xzux_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/maiy-tech-hub/components/blog/mdx-content.tsx","content":"'use client'\n\nimport { MDXRemote, type MDXRemoteSerializeResult } from 'next-mdx-remote'\nimport { Info, AlertCircle } from 'lucide-react'\n\n// ── Callout component ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nfunction Callout({\n  children,\n  type = 'note',\n}: {\n  children: React.ReactNode\n  type?: 'note' | 'warning' | 'tip'\n}) {\n  const styles = {\n    note: 'border-blue-500 bg-blue-50 dark:bg-blue-950/30 text-blue-800 dark:text-blue-200',\n    warning:\n      'border-amber-500 bg-amber-50 dark:bg-amber-950/30 text-amber-800 dark:text-amber-200',\n    tip: 'border-green-500 bg-green-50 dark:bg-green-950/30 text-green-800 dark:text-green-200',\n  }\n  const icons = { note: Info, warning: AlertCircle, tip: Info }\n  const Icon = icons[type]\n  return (\n    <div className={`my-6 rounded-lg border-l-4 p-4 ${styles[type]}`}>\n      <div className=\"flex items-start gap-3\">\n        <Icon className=\"h-5 w-5 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0 opacity-70\" />\n        <div className=\"flex-1 text-sm leading-relaxed\">{children}</div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  )\n}\n\n// ── MDX component map ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nconst components = {\n  Callout,\n  a: ({ children, href, ...props }: any) => (\n    <a\n      href={href}\n      className=\"text-primary underline-offset-4 hover:underline\"\n      target={href?.startsWith('http') ? '_blank' : undefined}\n      rel={href?.startsWith('http') ? 'noopener noreferrer' : undefined}\n      {...props}\n    >\n      {children}\n    </a>\n  ),\n  h2: ({ children, id, ...props }: any) => (\n    <h2 id={id} className=\"scroll-mt-24 font-bold text-2xl mt-10 mb-4\" {...props}>\n      {children}\n    </h2>\n  ),\n  h3: ({ children, id, ...props }: any) => (\n    <h3 id={id} className=\"scroll-mt-24 font-bold text-xl mt-8 mb-3\" {...props}>\n      {children}\n    </h3>\n  ),\n  table: ({ children, ...props }: any) => (\n    <div className=\"overflow-x-auto my-6\">\n      <table className=\"w-full border-collapse border border-border text-sm\" {...props}>\n        {children}\n      </table>\n    </div>\n  ),\n  th: ({ children, ...props }: any) => (\n    <th className=\"border border-border bg-muted px-4 py-2 text-left font-semibold\" {...props}>\n      {children}\n    </th>\n  ),\n  td: ({ children, ...props }: any) => (\n    <td className=\"border border-border px-4 py-2\" {...props}>\n      {children}\n    </td>\n  ),\n  // Inline code — no shiki needed\n  code: ({ children, className, ...props }: any) => {\n    if (!className) {\n      return (\n        <code className=\"px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded bg-muted text-sm font-mono text-primary/90\">\n          {children}\n        </code>\n      )\n    }\n    // Block code — will be handled by pre override\n    return <code className={className} {...props}>{children}</code>\n  },\n}\n\ninterface MDXContentProps {\n  source: MDXRemoteSerializeResult\n  highlightedHtml?: string // pre-highlighted HTML from server\n}\n\nexport function MDXContent({ source, highlightedHtml }: MDXContentProps) {\n  return (\n    <div className=\"prose-custom\">\n      {highlightedHtml ? (\n        <div dangerouslySetInnerHTML={{ __html: highlightedHtml }} />\n      ) : (\n        <MDXRemote {...source} components={components} />\n      )}\n    </div>\n  )\n}\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":109,"output":1208,"cacheRead":90516,"cacheWrite":1957,"totalTokens":93790,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776587032452,"responseId":"0633c4193a7ecbaaced3d2d80839b564"}}
