{"type":"message","id":"b9204ae0","parentId":"58f9a19f","timestamp":"2026-04-19T08:25:40.183Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me also fix the slow tab navigation issue. The problem might be that `next-mdx-remote/rsc` is slow because it's processing MDX on every request. Let me check if we should use static generation or add some caching.\n\nActually, the real issue is likely that the `tsx server/server.ts` dev server doesn't serve static assets as fast as the production build. Let me try running `yarn dev` instead and see if it's faster.\n\nBut actually, the more important fix for performance is to make sure the article pages are statically generated. Let me check if the article page has `export const dynamic = 'force-static'` or similar.","thinkingSignature":"5c6fbcbb6fb451a3064126d87497fa28217d4fff55eaed49fd468afe4100ca93"},{"type":"text","text":"**Fix 2: Page navigation performance** — add static generation:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_oxygso8q47pc_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/maiy-tech-hub/app/articles/[slug]/page.tsx","limit":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":110,"output":210,"cacheRead":97735,"cacheWrite":976,"totalTokens":99031,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776587133739,"responseId":"0633c47f06a04dea7a168a6b7c6bd527"}}
