{"type":"message","id":"2ec64742","parentId":"9b7b0a99","timestamp":"2026-04-19T08:25:56.724Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Actually, let me think about the slow navigation issue more carefully. The problem might be:1. `tsx server/server.ts` is running in development mode — every page request re-compiles MDX with shiki (slow!)\n2. The `rehype-shiki` plugin needs to compile each code block, which takes time\n\nFor development speed, I should NOT use shiki in dev mode. Instead, I should either:\n- Use a lighter highlighter like `highlight.js` for dev\n- Or pre-highlight during build only\n\nBut actually the real issue is the custom server running in dev mode. The `tsx server/server.ts` runs Next.js in dev mode with hot reload, which is slow.\n\n\nThe core issue is that `tsx server/server.ts` is just wrapping `next dev` in dev mode, which re-evaluates everything on each request and processes shiki on the fly. I should either switch to a production build with `next start` or find a way to cache the shiki compilation. The quickest wins are enabling ISR to cache pages for a set period, moving MDX processing out of the hot path, and potentially switching to a lighter syntax highlighter for development.\n\nLet me test the current build performance first and see if `next start` on the production build performs better than the dev server. I should also check the article listing page since navigation between tabs like articles → music could be slow if those pages aren't pre-rendered.","thinkingSignature":"558406b4961776d859b080a190967d9b59926473ffb8d6be29ee24be7b189617"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_bhib6nyxffez_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/maiy-tech-hub && yarn build 2>&1 | grep -E \"Type error|✓|Failed|pages|Error\" | head -10","yieldMs":50000,"timeout":120}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":114,"out