{"type":"message","id":"1f7d414e","parentId":"4c58c850","timestamp":"2026-04-19T08:27:09.408Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_x6l9oafb5itm_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import { MDXRemote } from 'next-mdx-remote/rsc'\n              <MDXRemote source={article.content} options={mdxOptions} />"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":23,"aggregated":"import { MDXRemote } from 'next-mdx-remote/rsc'\n              <MDXRemote source={article.content} options={mdxOptions} />","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776587229383}}
{"type":"message","id":"c7fd44c1","parentId":"1f7d414e","timestamp":"2026-04-19T08:27:24.285Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `MDXRemote` from `next-mdx-remote/rsc` expects the `options` to be of type `SerializeOptions`. Let me check what that type looks like. The issue is that `mdxOptions` structure doesn't match.\n\nIn `next-mdx-remote/rsc`, the options structure is different. Let me look at the actual type.Actually, in `next-mdx-remote/rsc`, the `options` prop should be `SerializeOptions` which has `mdxOptions` as a nested property. But maybe the plugin types are conflicting.Let me try a different approach - use the MDX compilation separately with shiki and then pass the result to MDXRemote, or use `compile` + `run` from `mdx-bundler` approach.Actually, the simplest fix is to not use rehype-shiki as a plugin, but instead create a separate server-side function that pre-highlights code blocks and then injects the HTML.Let me take a different approach: instead of rehype-shiki plugin, I'll pre-process the MDX content server-side to highlight code blocks.","thinkingSignature":"f32a12c2c3b2df124e8a72c0c561b419d9509a3ba3f7c3487257335af594faab"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_soo3mzxbqgz1_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/maiy-tech-hub/lib/highlight-mdx.ts","content":"import { compile } from '@mdx-js/mdx'\nimport * as runtime from 'react/jsx-runtime'\nimport remarkGfm from 'remark-gfm'\nimport { codeToHtml } from 'shiki'\n\nexport async function compileMDXWithShiki(source: string) {\n  // Pre-highlight code blocks before MDX compilation\n  const highlighted = await highlightCodeBlocks(source)\n\n  const { default: Content } = await compile(highlighted, {\n    outputFormat: 'function-body',\n    remarkPlugins: [remarkGfm],\n    development: false,\n  })\n\n  return { default: Content }\n}\n\n// ── Highlighting ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nconst CODE_BLOCK_RE = /```(\\w*)\\n([\\s\\S]*?)```/g\n\nasync function highlightCodeBlocks(source: string): Promise<string> {\n  const matches = [...source.matchAll(CODE_BLOCK_RE)]\n  if (matches.length === 0) return source\n\n  // Collect all highlighted results in parallel\n  const highlights = await Promise.all(\n    matches.map(async (match) => {\n      const [full, lang, code] = match\n      const decoded = code.replace(/&lt;/g, '<').replace(/&gt;/g, '>').replace(/&amp;/g, '&')\n      const clean = decoded.replace(/^&amp;.*\\n?/, '')\n\n      let html: string\n      try {\n        html = await codeToHtml(clean.trimEnd(), {\n          lang: lang || 'text',\n          theme: 'github-dark',\n        })\n        // Wrap in a container div\n        html = html.replace('<pre ', '<div class=\"code-block\"><pre ').replace('</pre>', '</pre></div>')\n      } catch {\n        html = `<pre><code>${clean.replace(/</g, '&lt;').replace(/>/g, '&gt;')}</code></pre>`\n      }\n\n      return { full, html }\n    })\n  )\n\n  let result = source\n  for (const { full, html } of highlights) {\n    // Replace code block with HTML\n    result = result.replace(full, html)\n  }\n\n  return result\n}\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":109,"output":747,"cacheRead":99786,"cacheWrite":307,"totalTokens":100949,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776587229421,"responseId":"0633c4de5ee4a3aab6d2379daa0d4c6a"}}
