{"type":"message","id":"0928d6be","parentId":"545b912b","timestamp":"2026-04-19T08:27:39.606Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, that approach won't highlight the code blocks since I removed rehype-shiki and the MDXRemote isn't using the pre-highlighted version. Let me rethink this.\n\nThe issue is that the MDX compilation happens in the RSC rendering, and I want to pre-highlight code blocks before MDX compilation. But the pre-highlighting approach I created is separate.\n\nActually, the simplest approach that works: use `rehype-shiki` but properly type the options. Let me check what the exact error is.\n\nThe error was: `Type '{ mdxOptions: { remarkPlugins: ...; rehypePlugins: ...; }; }' is not assignable to type 'SerializeOptions'.`\n \nI think the problem is that I'm wrapping the options object in an extra `mdxOptions` layer that MDXRemote doesn't expect. Let me try passing the plugins directly without that wrapper.","thinkingSignature":"3f5b3444888e682d9a2376d22603c70da0615d6d37f0b686169282b48a43e0bc"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2wqynrtjv3ar_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/maiy-tech-hub && node -e \"const t = require('next-mdx-remote/rsc'); console.log(Object.keys(t))\"","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":114,"output":262,"cacheRead":100135,"cacheWrite":1240,"totalTokens":101751,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776587252566,"responseId":"0633c4f6df630f9ece9635a42f6d7a4e"}}
