{"type":"message","id":"3ce08bc9","parentId":"1d12198f","timestamp":"2026-04-19T08:27:49.821Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"There's a `compileMDX` export! Let me use that instead. This is the approach:\n\n```tsx\nimport { compileMDX } from 'next-mdx-remote/rsc'\nimport rehypeSlug from 'rehype-slug'\nimport rehypeAutolinkHeadings from 'rehype-autolink-headings'\nimport { codeToHtml } from 'shiki'\n\nexport default async function ArticlePage({ params }: Props) {\n  const { content } = await compileMDX({\n    source: article.content,\n    options: {\n      mdxOptions: {\n        remarkPlugins: [remarkGfm],\n        rehypePlugins: [\n          rehypeSlug,\n          [rehypeAutolinkHeadings, { behavior: 'wrap' }],\n          // rehype-shiki here\n        ],\n      },\n    },\n    components: ...\n  })\n}\n```\n\nI should use `compileMDX` instead, but the real issue is that `rehype-shiki` might be causing the type mismatch with the plugin configuration.\n\nLet me sidestep the typing problem entirely by pre-processing the MDX content with shiki before it reaches the compiler, then pass the already-highlighted code blocks to `compileMDX`.","thinkingSignature":"792e2154408a844d3fa3887e157418b2b1e1ebe16992906a5aedd064e5e343ef"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_gunbzvhkio4k_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/maiy-tech-hub/app/articles/[slug]/page.tsx","edits":[{"oldText":"import { MDXRemote } from 'next-mdx-remote/rsc'\nimport rehypeSlug from 'rehype-slug'\nimport rehypeAutolinkHeadings from 'rehype-autolink-headings'\nimport { compileMDXWithShiki } from '@/lib/highlight-mdx'","newText":"import { compileMDX } from 'next-mdx-remote/rsc'\nimport remarkGfm from 'remark-gfm'\nimport rehypeSlug from 'rehype-slug'\nimport rehypeAutolinkHeadings from 'rehype-autolink-headings'\nimport { codeToHtml } from 'shiki'"}]}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Hold