{"type":"message","id":"987c4d93","parentId":"df1fe59b","timestamp":"2026-04-19T08:30:09.368Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `compileMDX` returns an object with `content` (a React component), not `{ default: Content }`. Let me check the actual return type of `compileMDX`.From the `next-mdx-remote/rsc` source, `compileMDX` returns `{ content: ReactElement, frontmatter: object }`. So I should use `content` not `{ default: content }`.Wait, looking at the code more carefully:```tsx\nconst { content } = await compileMDX({  source: highlighted,\n  ...\n})\n```And then use `{content}` in JSX. That should be fine.But the error says `Property 'default' does not exist on type 'VFile'`. \n\nThe `compileMDX` function wraps `compile` internally, so I should use the `content` property directly from the return value rather than trying to destructure a `default` property. Let me check the actual API from the next-mdx-remote documentation to confirm what properties are available. I'm wondering if the issue is actually with how `@shikijs/rehype` is configured in the next.config rather than the MDXRemote options themselves. Let me step back and use a simpler approach instead—maybe just stick with `highlight.js` for syntax highlighting since it's more straightforward, and I can style the code blocks with the GitHub dark theme using basic CSS without needing complex rehype plugins.","thinkingSignature":"f0fa08c28242a72c73ed422ad01706ae7bfca70f4adf6b26aefa66595ef3dea2"},{"type":"text","text":"\nLet me simplify — dùng `highlight.js` thay vì shiki (shiki quá nặng cho dev):\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_mm7thkk8keb3_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/maiy-tech-hub && yarn add highlight.js 2>&1 | tail -3","timeout":20}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":103,"output":387,"cacheRead":108234,"cacheWrite":282,"totalTokens