{"type":"message","id":"52a6e1b8","parentId":"65928216","timestamp":"2026-04-19T08:37:16.174Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The production build doesn't have the prerender-manifest.json because the custom server uses dev mode. Let me go back to the dev server but just keep it running.Actually, the issue is that the custom server with `tsx server/server.ts` starts Next.js with `dev = process.env.NODE_ENV !== 'production'`. So if NODE_ENV=production, it tries to use the production build, but the custom server doesn't work well with the production build.Let me just go back to the dev server and focus on optimizing the navigation issue differently. The main fix for slow navigation is to:1. Pre-render all pages statically (which we do with `force-static`)2. \n\nReduce the JS bundle size, implement lazy loading for heavy components like YouTube embeds, and make sure the Next.js Link component handles navigation properly. Let me restart the dev server.","thinkingSignature":"13556247933033a99daa554fc06de74af841f77046576619aa47dbe8f2780e21"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_9o1du1twb6zd_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/maiy-tech-hub && nohup npx tsx server/server.ts > /tmp/maiy-ws.log 2>&1 &\necho \"PID: $!\"","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":376,"output":263,"cacheRead":118844,"cacheWrite":247,"totalTokens":119730,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776587828293,"responseId":"0633c735dcd02a6bfd564e706aac12e0"}}
