{"type":"message","id":"1a0fae4e","parentId":"07e7d718","timestamp":"2026-04-19T09:06:44.258Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_uwtd11qdsnxh_1","toolName":"image","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This hero section has a dark, neon-tech style, but there are a few clear layout and readability problems.\n\n### Overall look\n- The background is **very dark navy/purple** with a **futuristic network/grid pattern** made of thin glowing lines.\n- There are many **small floating pixel-like squares** in cyan, purple, and pink scattered across the screen.\n- The visual style feels like an **AI / coding / developer platform landing page**.\n\n### Top badge\n- At the top center there is a **pill-shaped label** that says:\n  - **“Nền tảng học CNTT hàng đầu Việt Nam”**\n- It has a soft purple/blue glow and rounded corners.\n- This badge looks fine stylistically, but it is a bit small compared to the large headline below.\n\n### Main headline\n- The main hero title is:\n  - **“MAIY Tech Hub”**\n- It is very large and uses a **gradient fill** from purple to blue.\n- This is the strongest visual element and is centered.\n- The typography is bold and attention-grabbing.\n\n### Subtitle / description\nUnder the heading, there is a multi-line Vietnamese description:\n\n- **“Kiến thức CNTT chuẩn chỉnh — từ CTDL & Giải thuật đến AI, Web Dev & DevOps. Code thật, giải thích dễ hiểu, hoàn toàn bằng tiếng Việt.”**\n\n#### Problems here:\n- The subtitle looks **slightly crowded**.\n- The line wrapping feels awkward, especially around:\n  - **“DevOps. Code thật…”**\n- The text is **close to the headline** and the spacing doesn’t feel fully balanced.\n- Some parts appear a bit washed out against the busy background.\n- The line breaks do not feel intentional, which hurts readability.\n\n### Small stats / supporting text\nBelow the subtitle there is a smaller line that appears to say:\n- **“10+ bài viết chất lượng · Phòng học live · Nhạc thư giãn”**\n\n#### Problems with the stats:\n- This text is **too small** relative to the rest of the hero.\n- It lacks contrast and is hard to read.\n- It doesn’t feel like actual “stats”; it reads more like a tiny feature list.\n- Because it is faint and small, it gets visually lost between the subtitle and the buttons.\n- It could benefit from:\n  - larger font\n  - stronger contrast\n  - icon separation\n  - better spacing\n\n### Scroll hint\nThere is also a small text label:\n- **“Cuộn xuống”**\nwith a small arrow below it.\n\n#### Problems:\n- This element feels **misplaced** and too subtle.\n- It seems squeezed into the space above the buttons.\n- It does not align cleanly with the rest of the content.\n- It adds clutter rather than helping the layout.\n\n### Buttons\nThere are two CTA buttons centered below the text:\n\n1. **“Khám phá bài viết”**\n   - Purple/blue gradient\n   - Large rounded rectangle\n   - Strong glow\n   - This is clearly the **primary CTA**\n\n2. **“Phòng học live”**\n   - Dark button with subtle border/glow\n   - Rounded rectangle\n   - Weaker emphasis than the left button\n\n#### Button issues:\n- The buttons are visually attractive, but:\n  - The spacing between them could be cleaner.\n  - The vertical placement feels slightly cramped because of the tiny text and scroll hint above.\n  - The right button looks a bit darker and less legible than the left one.\n- The primary button stands out well, but the secondary button may be too visually muted.\n\n---\n\n## Layout structure\nThe hero is essentially:\n1. Top badge\n2. Huge centered headline\n3. Subtitle paragraph\n4. Tiny feature/stat line\n5. Scroll hint\n6. Two centered buttons\n\nThis is a standard centered hero layout, but the execution has some alignment and spacing issues.\n\n---\n\n## Main visual/layout problems\n\n### 1. Text overlap / crowding\n- The subtitle, small feature line, and “Cuộn xuống” label are **stacked too tightly**.\n- While there may not be literal hard overlap, the elements feel **visually compressed**.\n- The busy neon background makes this worse.\n\n### 2. Stats are too small\n- The feature/stat line is **noticeably undersized**.\n- It is hard to scan and easy to miss.\n- It doesn’t have enough visual weight to support the hero.\n\n### 3. Poor spacing hierarchy\n- The headline is very strong, but everything below it feels **less intentionally spaced**.\n- There should be clearer separation between:\n  - subtitle\n  - features/stats\n  - scroll hint\n  - CTAs\n\n### 4. Alignment feels slightly inconsistent\n- The overall content is centered, but the **scroll hint and arrow** feel like they float awkwardly.\n- The text blocks don’t feel perfectly balanced vertically.\n\n### 5. Background competes with text\n- The glowing lines and floating squares create a strong atmosphere, but they also introduce **visual noise**.\n- Lighter text and smaller text become harder to read against this background.\n\n### 6. CTA area is crowded\n- The buttons are good individually, but the area around them includes too many small elements.\n- The **“Cuộn xuống”** prompt right above them reduces the clean call-to-action focus.\n\n---\n\n## What works well\n- Strong branding with **“MAIY Tech Hub”**\n- Modern tech aesthetic\n- Good use of gradient color for the hero title\n- Primary CTA button is attractive and clear\n- Visual tone matches a tech/education platform\n\n## What needs improvement\n- Increase readability of subtitle and small feature/stat text\n- Make stats larger and more structured\n- Reduce clutter around the CTA area\n- Improve spacing between hero elements\n- Tone down background noise behind text\n- Reposition or simplify the “Cuộn xuống” hint\n\n### Summary\nThe hero section looks stylish and modern, centered around a big gradient **“MAIY Tech Hub”** headline on a dark futuristic background. It includes a top badge, a descriptive subtitle, a tiny feature/stat line, a scroll hint, and two call-to-action buttons. The main issues are **small unreadable stats, crowded text spacing, weak hierarchy below the title, and slightly awkward alignment around the scroll hint and buttons**. The design has strong visual potential, but the lower half of the hero feels compressed and less polished."}],"details":{"model":"ahvholding/AHV-Holding-TroLy","image":"/root/.openclaw/media/inbound/file_9---ec4c41cf-d8da-471f-a170-9c00c21453a2.jpg","attempts":[]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776589604204}}
{"type":"message","id":"fc07d181","parentId":"1a0fae4e","timestamp":"2026-04-19T09:07:25.032Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I can see the issues clearly:\n1. The \"Cuộn xuống\" scroll hint is awkwardly placed between the stats and buttons\n2. The stats bar below the hero (10+ bài viết, etc.) is too small and cramped\n3. The stats bar is visually disconnected from the hero - it's below the hero section entirely, which looks odd\n\nLet me fix these:\n\n1. Remove the \"Cuộn xuống\" indicator (it's causing clutter)\n2. Make the hero CTA area cleaner - more spacing, remove the scroll hint\n3. Improve the stats bar - make it more visible, with icons, better layout\n\n\n4. Actually, I'm realizing the stats bar is rendered separately in the page, not inside the hero component itself. The real problem is that the hero ends with CTA buttons, then there's a stats section below, then a featured article section. I need to integrate the stats directly into the hero so they appear within it rather than as a disconnected section below.\n\nI should redesign the hero section to include the stats with better visual hierarchy and proper spacing, make them look like actual feature highlights, and remove the awkward \"Cuộn xuống\" text that's cluttering the layout. The key is making sure these stats are prominent enough to be noticed but don't overwhelm the main CTA.","thinkingSignature":"784f8d76e272902f7e74d6fae07f3f0c7fe9ab1d5512c4fd97f25d82b638c3b3"},{"type":"text","text":"Thấy rõ vấn đề — stats bé quá, scroll hint gây rối, hero không hài hòa. Mình fix toàn bộ:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_l3aldfsprw8x_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/maiy-tech-hub/components/blog/three-hero.tsx","content":"'use client'\n\nimport { useEffect, useRef } from 'react'\nimport * as THREE from 'three'\nimport { useRouter } from 'next/navigation'\nimport { BookOpen, Users, Headphones, Zap } from 'lucide-react'\n\nexport function ThreeHero() {\n  const mountRef = useRef<HTMLDivElement>(null)\n  const router = useRouter()\n\n  useEffect(() => {\n    const mount = mountRef.current\n    if (!mount) return\n\n    const scene = new THREE.Scene()\n    const camera = new THREE.PerspectiveCamera(75, mount.clientWidth / mount.clientHeight, 0.1, 1000)\n    camera.position.z = 30\n\n    const renderer = new THREE.WebGLRenderer({ antialias: true, alpha: true })\n    renderer.setSize(mount.clientWidth, mount.clientHeight)\n    renderer.setPixelRatio(Math.min(window.devicePixelRatio, 2))\n    renderer.setClearColor(0x000000, 0)\n    mount.appendChild(renderer.domElement)\n\n    // Particles\n    const particleCount = 300\n    const positions = new Float32Array(particleCount * 3)\n    const velocities: number[] = []\n    const colors = new Float32Array(particleCount * 3)\n\n    const colorPalette = [\n      new THREE.Color('#8b5cf6'),\n      new THREE.Color('#06b6d4'),\n      new THREE.Color('#3b82f6'),\n      new THREE.Color('#ec4899'),\n      new THREE.Color('#10b981'),\n    ]\n\n    for (let i = 0; i < particleCount; i++) {\n      positions[i * 3] = (Math.random() - 0.5) * 60\n      positions[i * 3 + 1] = (Math.random() - 0.5) * 60\n      positions[i * 3 + 2] = (Math.random() - 0.5) * 40\n\n      velocities.push(\n        (Math.random() - 0.5) * 0.02,\n        (Math.random() - 0.5) * 0.02,\n        (Math.random() - 0.5) * 0.01\n      )\n\n      const col = colorPalette[Math.floor(Math.random() * colorPalette.length)]\n      colors[i * 3] = col.r\n      colors[i * 3 + 1] = col.g\n      colors[i * 3 + 2] = col.b\n    }\n\n    const particleGeo = new THREE.BufferGeometry()\n    particleGeo.setAttribute('position', new THREE.BufferAttribute(positions, 3))\n    particleGeo.setAttribute('color', new THREE.BufferAttribute(colors, 3))\n\n    const particleMat = new THREE.PointsMaterial({\n      size: 0.4,\n      vertexColors: true,\n      transparent: true,\n      opacity: 0.85,\n      blending: THREE.AdditiveBlending,\n      depthWrite: false,\n    })\n\n    const particles = new THREE.Points(particleGeo, particleMat)\n    scene.add(particles)\n\n    // Lines\n    const linePositions: number[] = []\n    const lineColors: number[] = []\n\n    for (let i = 0; i < particleCount; i++) {\n      for (let j = i + 1; j < particleCount; j++) {\n        const dx = positions[i * 3] - positions[j * 3]\n        const dy = positions[i * 3 + 1] - positions[j * 3 + 1]\n        const dz = positions[i * 3 + 2] - positions[j * 3 + 2]\n        const dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy + dz * dz)\n        if (dist < 8) {\n          const alpha = 1 - dist / 8\n          linePositions.push(\n            positions[i * 3], positions[i * 3 + 1], positions[i * 3 + 2],\n            positions[j * 3], positions[j * 3 + 1], positions[j * 3 + 2]\n          )\n          const col = colorPalette[i % colorPalette.length]\n          lineColors.push(col.r * alpha, col.g * alpha, col.b * alpha)\n          lineColors.push(col.r * alpha, col.g * alpha, col.b * alpha)\n        }\n      }\n    }\n\n    const lineGeo = new THREE.BufferGeometry()\n    lineGeo.setAttribute('position', new THREE.BufferAttribute(new Float32Array(linePositions), 3))\n    lineGeo.setAttribute('color', new THREE.BufferAttribute(new Float32Array(lineColors), 3))\n\n    const lineMat = new THREE.LineBasicMaterial({\n      vertexColors: true,\n      transparent: true,\n      opacity: 0.3,\n      blending: THREE.AdditiveBlending,\n      depthWrite: false,\n    })\n\n    const lines = new THREE.LineSegments(lineGeo, lineMat)\n    scene.add(lines)\n\n    // Floating shapes\n    const shapes: THREE.Mesh[] = []\n    for (let i = 0; i < 6; i++) {\n      const geom = i % 2 === 0\n        ? new THREE.IcosahedronGeometry(Math.random() * 0.8 + 0.3, 0)\n        : new THREE.OctahedronGeometry(Math.random() * 0.6 + 0.2, 0)\n\n      const mat = new THREE.MeshBasicMaterial({\n        color: colorPalette[i % colorPalette.length],\n        wireframe: true,\n        transparent: true,\n        opacity: 0.2,\n      })\n\n      const mesh = new THREE.Mesh(geom, mat)\n      mesh.position.set(\n        (Math.random() - 0.5) * 50,\n        (Math.random() - 0.5) * 40,\n        (Math.random() - 0.5) * 20\n      )\n      mesh.userData = {\n        rotSpeed: {\n          x: (Math.random() - 0.5) * 0.005,\n          y: (Math.random() - 0.5) * 0.005,\n          z: (Math.random() - 0.5) * 0.003,\n        },\n      }\n      shapes.push(mesh)\n      scene.add(mesh)\n    }\n\n    // Mouse parallax\n    let mouseX = 0, mouseY = 0\n    const onMouse = (e: MouseEvent) => {\n      mouseX = (e.clientX / window.innerWidth - 0.5) * 2\n      mouseY = (e.clientY / window.innerHeight - 0.5) * 2\n    }\n    window.addEventListener('mousemove', onMouse)\n\n    let animId: number\n    const posAttr = particleGeo.getAttribute('position') as THREE.BufferAttribute\n\n    const animate = () => {\n      animId = requestAnimationFrame(animate)\n      const time = Date.now() * 0.001\n\n      for (let i = 0; i < particleCount; i++) {\n        posAttr.array[i * 3] += velocities[i * 3]\n        posAttr.array[i * 3 + 1] += velocities[i * 3 + 1]\n        posAttr.array[i * 3 + 2] += velocities[i * 3 + 2]\n        if (Math.abs(posAttr.array[i * 3]) > 30) velocities[i * 3] *= -1\n        if (Math.abs(posAttr.array[i * 3 + 1]) > 30) velocities[i * 3 + 1] *= -1\n        if (Math.abs(posAttr.array[i * 3 + 2]) > 20) velocities[i * 3 + 2] *= -1\n      }\n      posAttr.needsUpdate = true\n\n      shapes.forEach((mesh) => {\n        mesh.rotation.x += mesh.userData.rotSpeed.x\n        mesh.rotation.y += mesh.userData.rotSpeed.y\n        mesh.rotation.z += mesh.userData.rotSpeed.z\n      })\n\n      camera.position.x += (mouseX * 5 - camera.position.x) * 0.05\n      camera.position.y += (-mouseY * 5 - camera.position.y) * 0.05\n      camera.lookAt(scene.position)\n\n      lineMat.opacity = 0.15 + Math.sin(time) * 0.1\n      renderer.render(scene, camera)\n    }\n\n    animate()\n\n    const onResize = () => {\n      if (!mount) return\n      camera.aspect = mount.clientWidth / mount.clientHeight\n      camera.updateProjectionMatrix()\n      renderer.setSize(mount.clientWidth, mount.clientHeight)\n    }\n    window.addEventListener('resize', onResize)\n\n    return () => {\n      cancelAnimationFrame(animId)\n      window.removeEventListener('mousemove', onMouse)\n      window.removeEventListener('resize', onResize)\n      renderer.dispose()\n      if (mount.contains(renderer.domElement)) {\n        mount.removeChild(renderer.domElement)\n      }\n    }\n  }, [])\n\n  const stats = [\n    { icon: BookOpen, label: 'Bài viết', value: '10+', color: 'text-violet-400' },\n    { icon: Users, label: 'Chủ đề', value: '5', color: 'text-cyan-400' },\n    { icon: Headphones, label: 'Âm nhạc', value: '4 moods', color: 'text-pink-400' },\n    { icon: Zap, label: 'Phòng học', value: 'Live', color: 'text-emerald-400' },\n  ]\n\n  return (\n    <section className=\"relative w-full h-screen min-h-[700px] overflow-hidden flex flex-col items-center justify-center\">\n      {/* Three.js canvas */}\n      <div ref={mountRef} className=\"absolute inset-0 z-0\" />\n\n      {/* Gradient overlays */}\n      <div className=\"absolute inset-0 z-10 bg-gradient-to-b from-transparent via-transparent to-background/60\" />\n      <div className=\"absolute inset-0 z-10 bg-[radial-gradient(ellipse_at_center,rgba(139,92,246,0.1)_0%,transparent_70%)]\" />\n      <div className=\"absolute inset-0 z-10 bg-gradient-to-r from-transparent via-transparent to-transparent\" />\n\n      {/* Content */}\n      <div className=\"relative z-20 text-center px-6 max-w-4xl mx-auto w-full\">\n        {/* Badge */}\n        <div className=\"inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-1.5 rounded-full bg-violet-500/10 border border-violet-500/20 text-violet-300 text-sm font-medium mb-8 backdrop-blur-sm\">\n          <span className=\"w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-violet-400 animate-pulse\" />\n          Nền tảng học CNTT hàng đầu\n        </div>\n\n        {/* Title */}\n        <h1 className=\"text-5xl md:text-7xl lg:text-8xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-6 leading-[1.1]\">\n          <span className=\"bg-gradient-to-r from-violet-400 via-cyan-400 to-blue-400 bg-clip-text text-transparent drop-shadow-lg\">\n            MAIY Tech Hub\n          </span>\n        </h1>\n\n        {/* Subtitle */}\n        <p className=\"text-base md:text-lg text-white/60 mb-10 max-w-xl mx-auto leading-relaxed\">\n          Kiến thức CNTT chuẩn chỉnh — CTDL, AI, Web Dev, DevOps.\n          Code thật, giải thích dễ hiểu, hoàn toàn bằng tiếng Việt.\n        </p>\n\n        {/* CTA Buttons */}\n        <div className=\"flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-center gap-3 mb-14\">\n          <button\n            onClick={() => router.push('/articles')}\n            className=\"w-full sm:w-auto px-10 py-4 rounded-xl bg-gradient-to-r from-violet-600 to-blue-600 text-white font-semibold text-base shadow-xl shadow-violet-500/20 hover:shadow-violet-500/40 hover:scale-[1.02] active:scale-[0.98] transition-all\"\n          >\n            Khám phá bài viết\n          </button>\n          <button\n            onClick={() => router.push('/study')}\n            className=\"w-full sm:w-auto px-10 py-4 rounded-xl border border-white/20 bg-white/5 backdrop-blur-sm text-white font-medium text-base hover:bg-white/10 hover:border-white/30 transition-all\"\n          >\n            Phòng học live\n          </button>\n        </div>\n\n        {/* Stats row — prominent and large */}\n        <div className=\"inline-flex items-stretch gap-0 rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5 backdrop-blur-md overflow-hidden\">\n          {stats.map((stat, i) => (\n            <div\n              key={stat.label}\n              className={`flex items-center gap-3 px-6 py-4 ${i < stats.length - 1 ? 'border-r border-white/10' : ''}`}\n            >\n              <stat.icon className={`h-5 w-5 flex-shrink-0 ${stat.color}`} />\n              <div className=\"text-left\">\n                <div className={`text-lg font-bold leading-none ${stat.color}`}>{stat.value}</div>\n                <div className=\"text-white/40 text-xs mt-0.5\">{stat.label}</div>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n          ))}\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </section>\n  )\n}\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":1477,"output":3333,"cacheRead":132544,"cacheWrite":722,"totalTokens":138076,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776589604286,"responseId":"0633ce26548757c85d92f23603e9da81"}}
